ysia confirmed two more cases, bringing the total to 14. One of the cases was locally transmitted, the first in Malaysia.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/asia/se-asia/malaysia-confirms-two-new-patients-bringing-total-coronavirus-infections-count-to-14|title=Malaysia confirms two new patients, bringing total coronavirus infections count to 14|last1=Leong|first1=Trinna|website=The Straits Times|language=en|access-date=6 February 2020|date=6 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.scmp.com/news/asia/southeast-asia/article/3049350/coronavirus-malaysia-confirms-first-case-human|title=Coronavirus: Malaysia confirms first case of human transmission from Singaporte meeting, taking tally to 14|last1=Tashny|first1=Sukumaran|date=6 February 2020|website=South China Morning Post|publisher=South China Morning Post|language=English|accessdate=7 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200206232256/https://www.scmp.com/news/asia/southeast-asia/article/3049350/coronavirus-malaysia-confirms-first-case-human|archive-date=6 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n* Singapore confirmed two more cases, bringing the total to 30.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/health/coronavirus-singapore-confirms-two-more-cases-bringing-total-to-30|title=Coronavirus: Singapore confirms 2 new local cases; 1 appears to have no link to previous cases|website=The Straits Times|language=en|access-date=6 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200206140727/https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/health/coronavirus-singapore-confirms-two-more-cases-bringing-total-to-30|archive-date=6 February 2020|url-status=live|date=6 February 2020}}</ref>\n* Taiwan announced three more cases, bringing the total to 16.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.taiwannews.com.tw/en/news/3872792|title=Taiwan announces 3 more cases of Wuhan virus,...|last=News|first=Taiwan|website=Taiwan News}}</ref>\n\n* The United Kingdom saw the third case confirmed, 