talian man, in Tenerife, Canary Islands.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Jones |first1=Jessica |last2=Maler |first2=Sandra |title=Italian national becomes third case of coronavirus in Spain |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-spain/italian-national-becomes-third-case-of-coronavirus-in-spain-idUSKCN20I2JB |website=Reuters |accessdate=25 February 2020 |date=25 February 2020}}</ref>\n* Taiwan confirmed two more cases, bringing the total number to 30.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Chen |first1=Wei-ting |last2=Yeh |first2=Joseph |title=Two more COVID-19 cases reported, bringing Taiwan total to 30 |url=https://focustaiwan.tw/society/202002240011 |website=Focus Taiwan |accessdate=24 February 2020 |date=24 February 2020}}</ref>\n* The United States confirmed 18 more cases including evacuated passengers from the cruise ship, bringing the total number to 53.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Salo |first1=Jackie |title=US confirms 53 coronavirus cases, including evacuated cruise passengers |url=https://nypost.com/2020/02/24/us-confirms-53-coronavirus-cases-including-evacuated-cruise-passengers/ |website=New York Post |accessdate=25 February 2020 |date=24 February 2020}}</ref>\n* A patient in [[Sichuan]] province tested positive only on her 9th test.<ref>{{cite news|script-title=zh:\u56db\u5ddd\u65b0\u589e1\u786e\u8bca\u75c5\u4f8b \u6b64\u524d8\u6b21\u6838\u9178\u68c0\u6d4b\u9634\u6027\n|url=http://www.takungpao.com/news/232108/2020/0225/419734.html|newspaper=[[Ta Kung Pao]] |language=zh-cn |date=25 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== 25 February ===\n'''WHO''' Situation Report 36:<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/situation-reports/20200225-sitrep-36-covid-19.pdf?sfvrsn=2791b4e0_2|title=Situation Report 36|last=|first=|date=|website=World Health Organization|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=25 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n* Algeria reported its first case, an Italian man who arrived on 17 February.<ref>{{cite web |title=First coronavirus case in Algeria |url=https://www.jpost.com/Breaking-News/First-coronavirus-case-in-Algeria-618802 |publisher=Jerusalem Post |accessdate=25 February 2020}}</ref>\n* Austria reported its first two cases, two Italians living in Tyrol tested positive for the coronavirus.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/live/2020/feb/25/coronavirus-live-updates-outbreak-latest-news-italy-italia-deaths-symptoms-china-stocks-wall-street-dow-jones-economy-falls?page=with:block-5e550afd8f086a28115b2205#block-5e550afd8f086a28115b2205|title=Austria reports first two cases of coronavirus|date=25 February 2020|agency=AP|newspaper=[[The Guardian]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://orf.at/stories/3155602/|title=Zwei F\u00e4lle in Tirol best\u00e4tigt|language=de|date=25 February 2020|publisher=[[ORF (broadcaster)|ORF]]}}</ref> One of the couple was a receptionist at a hotel and as a result the hotel in the Alpine tourist hub of Innsbruck was sealed off in an effort to contain the outbreak.\n* Bahrain confirmed its second case, a Bahraini woman who had travelled from Iran through Dubai International Airport.<ref>{{cite web |title=Second case of coronavirus detected in Bahrain |date=23 February 2020 |url=http://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/gulf/2020/02/24/First-case-of-coronavirus-detected-in-Bahrain-.html |publisher=Al Arabiya |accessdate=25 February 2020}}</ref> This later increased to eight confirmed cases with the addition of two Bahraini men and four Saudi Arabian women.<ref>{{cite web |title=Eight coronavirus cases confirmed in Bahrain, including four Saudi Arabian women |date=24 February 2020 |url=http://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/gulf/2020/02/25/Six-new-coronavirus-cases-confirmed-in-Bahrain-bringing-total-to-eight.html |publisher=Al Arabiya |accessdate=25 February 2020}}</ref> Later on the same day, Bahrain updated the number of cases to 17, with all infected people travelling from Iran.<ref>{{cite web |title=Bahrain announces 17 cases of new coronavirus infection |url=https://gulfnews.com/world/gulf/bahrain/bahrain-announces-17-cases-of-new-coronavirus-infection-1.1582636110968 |publisher=[[Gulf News]] |date=25 February 2020}}</ref>  This total later rose again to 23 cases, again all having travelled from Iran.<ref>{{cite web |title=China coronavirus outbreak: All the latest updates |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/02/china-coronavirus-outbreak-latest-updates-200225003320810.html |publisher=Al Jazeera |accessdate=25 February 2020}}</ref>\n* Brazil Ministry of Health reported the first positive case of coronavirus in the country and South America, a 61-year-old man from [[S\u00e3o Paulo]], who travelled to [[Lombardy]], [[Italy]], between 9 and 21 February. He was showing mild symptoms and quarantined at home, the confirmation test was also positive.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/sp/sao-paulo/noticia/2020/02/25/ministerio-da-saude-investiga-possivel-paciente-com-coronavirus-em-sp-caso-foi-para-contraprova.ghtml|title=Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade investiga poss\u00edvel paciente com coronav\u00edrus em SP; caso foi para contraprova|website=G1|date=25 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www1.folha.uol.com.br/equilibrioesaude/2020/02/brasil-confirma-primeiro-caso-do-novo-coronavirus.shtml|title=Brasil confirma primeiro caso do novo coronav\u00edrus|website=Folha de S.Paulo|date=25 February 2020}}</ref>\n* Croatia announced its first case of the virus, with a patient hospitalised in the capital, Zagreb, who had travelled to Italy and stayed in Milan.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/live/2020/feb/25/coronavirus-live-updates-outbreak-latest-news-italy-italia-deaths-symptoms-china-stocks-wall-street-dow-jones-economy-falls?page=with:block-5e550d8a8f086a28115b222d#block-5e550d8a8f086a28115b222d|title=Croatia latest European country to confirm coronavirus case|date=25 February 2020|newspaper=[[The Guardian]]}}</ref>\n* France saw two additional cases: one was a French man returning 