 organizations were ordered to keep rents low and banks to keep interest low. A stimulus package is expected.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/02/12/world/asia/coronavirus-china-covid-19.html|title=Coronavirus Updates: China Seeks to Restart Economy While Fighting Outbreak|date=12 February 2020|work=The New York Times|access-date=12 February 2020|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref>\n\n[[Honghu|Honghu, Hubei]] began an official investigation into a controversial fine of \u00a542630 (US$6110.54) on a local pharmacy for selling 44,000 single-use masks stocked at \u00a50.6 (US$0.086) each for \u00a51 (US$0.143) each, as it violated a province-wide ban on selling medical items related to the epidemic 15% above the stocking price during the epidemic. The move came after heavy criticism online after the fining became known.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sohu.com/a/372724100_260616|title=6\u89d2\u53e3\u7f69\u53561\u5143\u88ab\u7f5a4\u4e07? \u6e56\u5317\u6d2a\u6e56\u5df2\u5bf9\u8be5\u5904\u7f5a\u542f\u52a8\u91cd\u65b0\u8c03\u67e5_\u6bdb\u5148\u751f|website=www.sohu.com|language=en|access-date=13 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.guancha.cn/politics/2020_02_13_535998.shtml|language=zh |script-title=zh:\u6e56\u5317\u6d2a\u6e56\u4e00\u836f\u623f6\u6bdb\u53e3\u7f69\u53561\u5143\u88ab\u7f5a\u8fd16\u4e07\uff0c\u5b98\u65b9\uff1a\u91cd\u65b0\u8c03\u67e5|website=www.guancha.cn|access-date=13 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== 13 February ===\nHubei released 1.3 million masks for civil use, providing pharmacies at \u00a51 each and requiring them to sell at the \"affordable price\" of \u00a52 (US$0.287) each.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bjnews.com.cn/news/2020/02/13/688878.html|language=zh |script-title=zh:\u6e56\u5317130\u4e07\u53ea\u6c11\u7528\u53e3\u7f69\u6295\u5411\u5e02\u573a \u8fdb\u4ef71\u5143\u96f6\u552e2\u5143|last=www.bjnews.com.cn|website=www.bjnews.com.cn|access-date=13 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn Hubei, The Zhangjiawan District of [[Shiyan]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bjnews.com.cn/news/2020/02/13/689015.html|language=zh |script-title=zh:\u6e56\u5317\u5927\u609f\u53bf\u5b9e\u65bd\u6218\u65f6\u7ba1\u5236|last=www.bjnews.com.cn|website=www.bjnews.com.cn|access-date=14 February 2020}}</ref> entered wartime control starting 00:00, as well as [[Dawu County, Hubei|Dawu County]] in [[Xiaogan]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jiemian.com/article/3977471.html|language=zh |script-title=zh:\u6e56\u5317\u5341\u5830\u5f20\u6e7e\u533a13\u65e5\u96f6\u65f6\u8d77\u6218\u65f6\u7ba1\u5236{{!}}\u754c\u9762\u65b0\u95fb \u00b7 \u5feb\u8baf|website=www.jiemian.com|access-date=14 February 2020}}</ref> the status to be reviewed at least once every 14 days.\n\nHubei postponed business resumption and start of new semester across the province; businesses were not to resume before 24:00 on 20 Feb.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jiemian.com/article/3979654.html|language=zh |script-title=zh:\u6e56\u5317\u7ee7\u7eed\u5ef6\u8fdf\u590d\u5de5\u5f00\u5b66\uff1a\u5404\u7c7b\u4f01\u4e1a\u4e0d\u65e9\u4e8e2\u670820\u65e524\u65f6\u524d\u590d\u5de5{{!}}\u754c\u9762\u65b0\u95fb \u00b7 \u5feb\u8baf|website=www.jiemian.com|access-date=14 February 2020}}</ref> Guangxi prohibited the start of new semester before 1 March.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jiemian.com/article/3981924.html |language=zh-cn |script-title=zh:\u5e7f\u897f\u518d\u6b21\u8c03\u6574\u5ef6\u8fdf\u5f00\u5b66\u65f6\u95f4\uff0c\u5404\u7ea7\u5404\u7c7b\u5b66\u68213\u67081\u65e5\u524d\u4e0d\u5f97\u5f00\u5b66{{!}}\u754c\u9762\u65b0\u95fb \u00b7 \u5feb\u8baf|website=www.jiemian.com|access-date=14 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nWuhan enacts a new rule prohibiting people from leaving their neighbourhoods for non-medical reasons, updating the curfew to a full lockdown.<ref>{{cite news |title=Wuhan Sharply Tightens Quarantines on Residents: Virus Update |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-02-13/u-s-ramps-up-criticism-hubei-data-awaited-virus-update |accessdate=15 February 2020 |