om|access-date=15 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n[[Huanggang]] decided to convert another hospital as a secondary medical institution for COVID-19, after [[Dabie Mountain Regional Medical Centre]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jiemian.com/article/3986588.html|language=zh |script-title=zh:\u6e56\u5317\u9ec4\u5188\u518d\u9020\u4e00\u6240\u5e94\u6025\u540e\u5907\u533b\u9662{{!}}\u754c\u9762\u65b0\u95fb \u00b7 \u5feb\u8baf|website=www.jiemian.com|access-date=15 February 2020}}</ref> [[Xiantao|Xiantao, Hubei]] implemented mask ex-factory price control, requiring the ex-factory price of single use medical masks not to exceed \u00a51.20 (US$0.172) each and non-medical ones \u00a51.00 (US$0.143) each.\n\nBeijing required all persons returning to the city to self-quarantine for 14 days.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jiemian.com/article/3986548.html|language=zh |script-title=zh:\u5317\u4eac\uff1a\u5373\u65e5\u8d77\u6240\u6709\u8fd4\u4eac\u4eba\u5458\u5e94\u5c45\u5bb6\u6216\u96c6\u4e2d\u89c2\u5bdf14\u5929|last=|first=|date=14 February 2020|website=jiemian.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=15 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nShenzhen Metro would start using [[real-name system]] starting 16 Feb for epidemic tracing, with passengers able to self-register the carriages they ride in by scanning the QR code in the train.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.ifeng.com/c/7u3nte8SRX4 |language=zh-cn |script-title=zh:\u5468\u65e5\u8d77\u6df1\u5733\u5730\u94c1\u5168\u9762\u5b9e\u540d\u5236\u4e58\u8f66\uff01\u4e58\u5ba2\u51fa\u884c\u4fe1\u606f\u53ef\u67e5\u8be2\u53ef\u8ffd\u6eaf|work=[[Ifeng]] News|access-date=14 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe Office of the State Council Education Steering Committee prohibited all after-school training institutions from conducting offline training in any form.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jiemian.com/article/3985044.html|language=zh-Hans |script-title=zh:\u56fd\u52a1\u9662\u6559\u7763\u59d4\u529e\u516c\u5ba4\uff1a\u4e25\u7981\u4efb\u4f55\u6821\u5