avirus-china.html|title=Hong Kong Reports First Death From Coronavirus Outbreak|last=Times|first=The New York|date=3 February 2020|via=NYTimes.com|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200206204957/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/02/03/world/asia/coronavirus-china.html|archive-date=6 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIndia invalidated all e-visas given to Chinese passport holders since 15 January. It also has stopped giving out new e-visas to Chinese passport holders.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/business/india-business/india-temporarily-suspends-e-visa-for-travellers-from-china/articleshow/73903341.cms|title=India temporarily suspends e-visa for travellers from China - Times of India|last=4 Feb|first=Saurabh Sinha {{!}} TNN {{!}} Updated|last2=2020|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=5 February 2020|last3=Ist|first3=14:11}}</ref>  India also gave a travel advisory to not travel to China.  The travel advisory also stated that anyone who comes to knowledge that had visited China since 15 January could get quarantined.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://weather.com/en-IN/india/news/news/2020-02-03-coronavirus-india-issues-fresh-travel-advisory-china|title=Coronavirus: India Issues Fresh Travel Advisory for China|website=The Weather Channel|language=en-US|access-date=5 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200206091435/https://weather.com/en-IN/india/news/news/2020-02-03-coronavirus-india-issues-fresh-travel-advisory-china|archive-date=6 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nSeveral exhibitors and South Korea's [[Black Eagles]] have decided to pull out of the [[Singapore Airshow]]. This comes as the virus situation worsens.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Wong |first1=Kai Yi |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/business/companies-markets/some-exhibitors-drop-out-of-singapore-airshow-due-to-wuhan-virus |title=Coronavirus keeps exhibitors away from Singapore Airshow; Korea's Black Eagles not com