-coronavirus-outbreak-air-india-suspends-delhi-hong-kong-flights-from-feb-8/22546155|archive-date=7 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nAn aviation conference during the [[Singapore Airshow]] is cancelled to allow leaders to deal with the coronavirus. This comes after 16 exhibitors pulled out of the Airshow.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Wong |first1=Kai Yi |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/business/economy/major-summit-on-eve-of-singapore-airshow-canceled-on-coronavirus-fears |title=Singapore Airshow to go ahead despite fewer exhibitors, with stepped-up coronavirus measures |access-date=24 February 2020 |website=The Straits Times |date=4 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n[[World Health Organization]] (WHO) released Novel coronavirus (2019-nCoV) Donor Alert. The document describes the current situation, mentions the strategic Global Preparedness and Response Plan including desription of the main elements of the strategy. The risk assessed was stated as:\n\n* Very high for China\n* High at the regional level\n* High at the global level\n\nThe required funding for WHO activities (Feb to Apr 2020) is stated at US$ 675.5 million GLOBAL RESOURCE REQUIREMENT and US$ 61.5 million WHO RESOURCE REQUIREMENT <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/donor-alert.pdf|title=Novel coronavirus (2019-nCoV) Donor Alert|last=|first=|date=February 4, 2020|website=WHO|publisher=WHO|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200406002423/https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/donor-alert.pdf|archive-date=April 6, 2020|access-date=}}</ref>\n=== 5 February ===\nUnited Airlines and [[American Airlines]] suspended US flights to and from Hong Kong.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/travel/2020/02/04/coronavirus-outbreak-united-american-suspend-hong-kong-flights/4659726002/|title=Coronavirus outbreak: United, American suspend flights to and from Hong Kong|last=Tate|first=Curtis|website=USA TODAY|language=en-US|access-date=5 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200206150509/https://www.usatoday.com/story/travel/2020/02/04/coronavirus-outbreak-united-american-suspend-hong-kong-flights/4659726002/|archive-date=6 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.scmp.com/news/world/united-states-canada/article/3049069/coronavirus-united-airlines-suspends-us-flights-and|title=Coronavirus: United Airlines suspends US flights to and from Hong Kong|date=5 February 2020|website=South China Morning Post|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200206090844/https://www.scmp.com/news/world/united-states-canada/article/3049069/coronavirus-united-airlines-suspends-us-flights-and|archive-date=6 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Cathay Pacific]] asked all of its 27,000 employees to take three weeks of unpaid leave in order to preserve cash during the virus epidemic.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.scmp.com/news/hong-kong/transport/article/3049132/coronavirus-cathay-pacific-asks-all-27000-employees-take|title=Cathay Pacific asks its 27,000 employees to take three weeks unpaid leave|date=5 February 2020|website=South China Morning Post|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200206132050/https://www.scmp.com/news/hong-kong/transport/article/3049132/coronavirus-cathay-pacific-asks-all-27000-employees-take|archive-date=6 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nHundreds more Americans were evacuated by two planes from Wuhan to the United States, landing in this case at [[Travis Air Force Base]] near Sacramento, California. One of the planes would continue on to [[Marine Corps Air Station Miramar]] in San Diego. All evacuees would undergo a two-week quarantine. \"Inbound evacuation flights to Wuhan were using their cargo space to deliver donated medical supplies for coronavirus relief efforts.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/world/coronavirus-updates-latest-news-outbreak-global-response-n1130406|title=Coronavirus updates: The latest news on the outbreak and the global response|website=NBC News|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200206073308/https://www.nbcnews.com/news/world/coronavirus-updates-latest-news-outbreak-global-response-n1130406|archive-date=6 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> A 12th US case of coronavirus was confirmed in [[Dane County, Wisconsin]].\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nypost.com/2020/02/05/wisconsin-coronavirus-case-brings-total-infected-in-us-to-12/|title=Wisconsin coronavirus case brings total infected in US to 12|last=Lapin|first=Tamar|date=5 February 2020|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200206192009/https://nypost.com/2020/02/05/wisconsin-coronavirus-case-brings-total-infected-in-us-to-12/|archive-date=6 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nbc15.com/content/news/First-coronavirus-case-in-Wisconsin-confirmed-567592081.html|title=Dane County resident is Wisconsin's first confirmed coronavirus case|author=|website=www.nbc15.com|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200206141253/https://www.nbc15.com/content/news/First-coronavirus-case-in-Wisconsin-confirmed-567592081.html|archive-date=6 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nHong Kong announced the beginning of a mandatory two-week quarantine for all visitors from mainland China or Macau.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-china-51389490|title=Hong Kong to quarantine mainland China visitors|date=5 February 2020|via=www.bbc.com|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200206231927/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-china-51389490|archive-date=6 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"auto17\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.scmp.com/news/china/politics/article/3049245/coronavirus-taiwan-restricts-travellers-hong-kong-and-macau|title=Taiwan restricts travellers from Hong Kong and Macau amid crisis|date=6 February 2020|website=South China Morning Post|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200206061021/https://www.scmp.com/news/china/politics/article/3049245/coronavirus-taiwan-restricts-travellers-hong-kong-and-macau|archive-date=6 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n[[Taiwan]] banned entry of non-citizens who have been to mainland China, Hong Kong or Macau within the past 14 days.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.scmp.com/news/china/society/article/3048798/coronavirus-taiwan-deadly-virus-h1n1-flu|title=Taiwan slaps coronavirus entry ban on foreigners from mainland China|date=4 February 2020|website=South China Morning Post|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200206031642/https://www.scmp.com/news/china/society/article/3048798/coronavirus-taiwan-deadly-virus-h1n1-flu|archive-date=6 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"auto17\" />\n\nWith the US CDC's endorsement, [[Colombia]] INS confirmed that it to be the first country in Latin America that might detect the novel coronavirus without sending samples to foreign centers.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.eltiempo.com/salud/prueba-para-detectar-el-coronavirus-en-colombia-458712|title=As\u00ed es la prueba que har\u00e1 Colombia para detectar el coronavirus|last=Tiempo|first=Casa Editorial El|date=4 February 2020|website=El Tiempo}}</ref>\n\nCanadian [[Minister of Foreign Affairs (Canada)|Minister of Foreign Affairs]] [[Fran\u00e7ois-Philippe Champagne]] advised all Canadians in China but outside the quarantine zone to leave the country \"via commercial means\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://nationalpost.com/news/canada/canadians-get-out-of-china-even-if-it-means-taking-commercial-flight-foreign-affairs-minister|title=Canadians, get out of China by any means possible: foreign affairs minister|date=5 February 2020|accessdate=5 February 2020|website=National Post}}</ref>\n\n[[India]] starts scanning passengers in flights coming from 