its Times|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200206144535/https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/coronavirus-employers-must-notify-mom-of-workers-returning-from-china-100-a-day-for-those|archive-date=6 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nPanic buying of consumer goods was reported in Hong Kong due to rumors of an impending quarantine.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.scmp.com/news/hong-kong/health-environment/article/3049410/coronavirus-hongkongers-panic-buying-rice-toilet|title=Panic buying rages as Hong Kong government silent on coming quarantine move|date=6 February 2020|website=South China Morning Post|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200206165400/https://www.scmp.com/news/hong-kong/health-environment/article/3049410/coronavirus-hongkongers-panic-buying-rice-toilet|archive-date=6 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n[[Virgin Atlantic|Virgin]], [[KLM]], [[Air France]], [[American Airlines]] (not including the  Hong Kong route), and [[Iberia (airline)|Iberia]] extended their current flight suspensions till sometime in March.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/world-news/coronavirus-outbreak-airlines-extend-china-flight-suspensions-over-coronavirus-fears-2176157|title=Airlines Extend China Flight Suspensions Amid Coronavirus Outbreak|website=NDTV.com|access-date=6 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200206231755/https://www.ndtv.com/world-news/coronavirus-outbreak-airlines-extend-china-flight-suspensions-over-coronavirus-fears-2176157|archive-date=6 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2020/02/06/reuters-america-update-1-klm-extends-ban-on-flights-to-china-until-mid-march.html|title=UPDATE 1-KLM extends ban on flights to China until mid-March|date=6 February 2020|website=CNBC|language=en|access-date=6 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200206231757/https://www.cnbc.com/2020/02/06/reuters-america-update