is is only the second time Singapore has activated Code Orange; the first was for the [[2009 flu pandemic|swine flu (H1N1) pandemic of 2009]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/health/coronavirus-new-measures-to-kick-in-as-singapore-moves-to-code-orange|title=Singapore raises coronavirus outbreak alert to Orange: What does it mean?|date=7 February 2020|website=The Straits Times|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200207120712/https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/health/coronavirus-new-measures-to-kick-in-as-singapore-moves-to-code-orange|archive-date=7 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Similar to reactions in Hong Kong the previous day, [[panic buying]] of groceries and consumer goods ensued.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/health/coronavirus-fairprice-chief-urges-calm-amid-panic-buying-of-groceries-singapores|title=Coronavirus: Politicians, supermarkets urge calm amid panic-buying of groceries|date=7 February 2020|website=The Straits Times}}</ref>\n\nTwo Hong Kong jewelry trade fairs, hosted by the [[Hong Kong Trade Development Council]], got rescheduled due to the virus epidemic.<ref name=\":13\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/anthonydemarco/2020/02/06/two-hong-kong-jewelry-trade-fairs-are-rescheduled-due-to-coronavirus/|title=Two Hong Kong Jewelry Trade Fairs Are Rescheduled Due To Coronavirus|last=DeMarco|first=Anthony|website=Forbes|language=en|access-date=7 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200207002750/https://www.forbes.com/sites/anthonydemarco/2020/02/06/two-hong-kong-jewelry-trade-fairs-are-rescheduled-due-to-coronavirus/|archive-date=7 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>  [[Art Basel Hong Kong]] international art fair, that was being held in March also gets cancelled due to the virus epidemic.<ref name=\":13\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://abcnews.go.com/Health/wireStory/latest-hong-kong-cancels-major-art-fair-amid-68814096|title=