 is country's second coronavirus case|date=9 February 2020|work=Reuters|access-date=9 February 2020|language=en}}</ref>\n\n* Taiwan confirmed its eighteenth case.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.taiwannews.com.tw/en/news/3873765|title=Taiwan records 18th coronavirus case, patient...|first=Taiwan|last=News|website=Taiwan News}}</ref>\n\n* United Kingdom confirmed its fourth case.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gov.uk/government/news/cmo-confirms-fourth-case-of-coronavirus-in-england|title=CMO confirms fourth case of coronavirus in England|website=GOV.UK}}</ref>\n\n* Vietnam confirmed its fourteenth case, a 55-year-old woman in [[V\u0129nh Ph\u00fac]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://vnexpress.net/suc-khoe/them-mot-nguoi-vinh-phuc-duong-tinh-ncov-4052445.html|title=Th\u00eam m\u1ed9t ng\u01b0\u1eddi V\u0129nh Ph\u00fac d\u01b0\u01a1ng t\u00ednh nCoV|website=VnExpress|date=9 February 2020|accessdate=9 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n* Six more cases were confirmed aboard {{ship||Diamond Princess|ship|2}}, bringing the total number of cases on the ship to 70, with Japan having 96 cases.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Hodo |first1=Chikafumi |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-02-09/japan-finds-6-more-coronavirus-cases-on-cruise-ship-tv-asahi |title=Japan Finds Six More Coronavirus Cases on Cruise Ship |work=Bloomberg |date=9 February 2020 |access-date=9 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2020/02/09/world/coronavirus-sars-diamond-princess#.XkACJXlGT3A |title=Japan confirms six more cases from quarantined cruise ship as coronavirus deaths surpasses SARS' toll |work=The Japan Times |date=9 February 2020 |access-date=9 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== 10 February ===\n'''WHO''' Situation Report 21:<ref>{{Citation|title=Novel Coronavirus(2019-nCoV) Situation Report - 21|url=https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/situation-reports/20200210-sitrep-21-ncov.pdf?sfvrsn=947679ef_2}}</ref>\n\n* Hong Kong confirmed six more cases, bringing