o caso do novo coronav\u00edrus|website=Folha de S.Paulo|date=25 February 2020}}</ref>\n* Croatia announced its first case of the virus, with a patient hospitalised in the capital, Zagreb, who had travelled to Italy and stayed in Milan.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/live/2020/feb/25/coronavirus-live-updates-outbreak-latest-news-italy-italia-deaths-symptoms-china-stocks-wall-street-dow-jones-economy-falls?page=with:block-5e550d8a8f086a28115b222d#block-5e550d8a8f086a28115b222d|title=Croatia latest European country to confirm coronavirus case|date=25 February 2020|newspaper=[[The Guardian]]}}</ref>\n* France saw two additional cases: one was a French man returning from a trip in the Lombardy region of Italy; the other was a young Chinese woman returning to France from a trip to China. This took the total number of cases in the country to 14.<ref>{{cite web |title=Coronavirus news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/health/coronavirus-news-live-uk-italy-outbreak-travel-advice-symptoms-latest-today-a9356296.html |newspaper=The Independent |accessdate=25 February 2020}}</ref>\n* Germany saw a case identified in the state of North Rhine-Westphalia of a person recently returned from Italy, taking the country's cases to 17. Another man was later confirmed to be positive, bringing the total number to 18.<ref>{{cite web |title=Man infected with coronavirus in Germany after Italy trip |url=https://www.jpost.com/Breaking-News/Southern-German-state-confirms-coronavirus-case-618810 |website=The Jerusalem Post |accessdate=26 February 2020 |date=26 February 2020}}</ref>\n* Hong Kong confirmed three more cases, bringing the total number to 84.<ref>{{cite web |title=Confirmed coronavirus cases in Hong Kong increase to 84 |url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/world/2020/feb/25/confirmed-coronavirus-cases-in-hong-kong-increase-to-84-2108349.html |website=The New Indian Express |accessdate=26 February 2020 |date=25 February 2020}}</ref>\n* Iranian officials confirmed the death toll was officially now 16. There were 34 more cases, bringing the total number to 95.<ref>{{cite web |title=Iran says coronavirus death toll reaches 16, 95 infected |url=https://nationalpost.com/pmn/health-pmn/iran-says-coronavirus-death-toll-reaches-16-95-infected |website=National Post |accessdate=26 February 2020 |date=25 February 2020}}</ref> The same day, Iranian MP [[Mahmoud Sadeghi]] confirmed he had tested positive for the virus,<ref>{{cite web |title=Iranian MP Mahmoud Sadeghi says he tested positive for coronavirus |date=24 February 2020 |url=https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/02/25/Iranian-MP-Mahmoud-Sadeghi-says-he-tested-positive-for-coronavirus.html |publisher=Al Arabiya |accessdate=25 February 2020}}</ref> along with [[Iraj Harirchi]], the Deputy Minister for Health, who had the previous day been part of a press conference about Iran's handling of the virus.<ref>{{cite web |title=Iran's deputy health minister tests positive for coronavirus |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/02/iran-deputy-health-minister-tests-positive-coronavirus-200225131520852.html |publisher=Al Jazeera |accessdate=25 February 2020}}</ref>\n* Iraq confirmed five more cases - an Iranian student and a family of four who had arrived from Iran, taking the total number of cases to 6.<ref>{{cite web |title=Iranian student, family of 4 are latest coronavirus cases in Iraq: Ministry |date=24 February 2020 |url=http://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/2020/02/25/Iranian-student-in-Iraq-is-the-latest-confirmed-coronavirus-case-Health-ministry.html |publisher=AL Arabiya |accessdate=25 February 2020}}</ref>\n* Italy confirmed 94 new cases, bringing the total to 323 spread across nine different administrative regions. Three more deaths were also confirmed, bringing the total number to 10.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Bocci |first1=Michele |title=Coronavirus, 325 casi in Italia. Altri tre morti in Lombardia e uno in Veneto, le vittime diventano 11 (in Italian) |