homas |title=South Korea coronavirus cases near 1,000; 11 dead |url=https://www.upi.com/Top_News/World-News/2020/02/25/South-Korea-coronavirus-cases-near-1000-11-dead/4761582619827/ |website=UPI |accessdate=26 February 2020 |date=25 February 2020}}</ref> Among those infected included a [[Korean Air]] crew member.<ref>{{cite web |title=One of Korean Air's cabin crew tests positive for coronavirus |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/asia/east-asia/one-of-korean-airs-cabin-crew-tests-positive-for-coronavirus |website=The Straits Times |accessdate=29 February 2020 |date=25 February 2020}}</ref>\n* Spain, Canary Islands: on the island of Tenerife two Italian hotel guests tested positive for the virus. This resulted in hundreds of guests at the H10 Costa Adeje Palace hotel being isolated to facilitate further testing and to halt the spread of the disease.<ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus: Tenerife hotel with hundreds of guests locked down |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-51627597 |accessdate=25 February 2020|work=BBC News |date=25 February 2020 }}</ref>  Later in the day, the first case was reported in mainland Spain, with a woman from Catalonia, who had recently returned from Italy, diagnosed in Barcelona.<ref>{{cite web |title=Woman in Barcelona tests positive to coronavirus, the first confirmed case on mainland Spain |url=https://www.thelocal.es/20200225/woman-in-barcelona-tests-positive-to-coronavirus-the-first-confirmed-case-in-mainland-spain |publisher=The Local.ES |accessdate=25 February 2020}}</ref> A seventh case was confirmed in the late evening by the  Madrid regional government.<ref>{{cite web |title=Coronavirus: Europe on alert as four more deaths reported in Italy \u2013 updates |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/live/2020/feb/25/coronavirus-live-updates-outbreak-latest-news-italy-italia-deaths-symptoms-china-stocks-wall-street-dow-jones-economy-falls |newspaper=The Guardian |accessdate=25 February 2020}}</ref>\n* Switzerland's government announced the first infection in the country.<ref name=\"Switzerland\">{{cite news|url=https://www.dw.com/en/coronavirus-updates-us-criticizes-iran-and-china-over-the-their-handling-of-the-outbreak/a-52516885|title=Coronavirus updates: US criticizes Iran and China over the their handling of the outbreak|date=25 February 2020|publisher=[[Deutsche Welle]]}}</ref><ref name=\"Switzerland_de\">{{cite news|url=https://www.blick.ch/news/coronavirus-erster-bestaetigter-fall-von-coronavirus-in-der-schweiz-id15767285.html|title=Erster best\u00e4tigter Fall in der Schweiz|language=de|date=25 February 2020|publisher=[[Blick]]}}</ref>\n* Taiwan confirmed one more case, an 11-year-old boy, bringing the total number to 31.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Strong |first1=Matthew |title=Taiwan's coronavirus case No. 31 is 11-year-old grandson of a previous patient |url=https://www.taiwannews.com.tw/en/news/3881028 |website=Taiwan News |accessdate=26 February 2020 |date=25 February 2020}}</ref>\n* Thailand reported two more cases, taking its total to 37. The two new cases, both Thai nationals, were people who were being monitored due to the travel history of others who had travelled to countries with infection  risks.<ref>{{cite web |title=Thailand reports two new COVID-19 cases, bringing total to 37 |url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asia/thailand-covid19-coronavirus-cases-12468314 |website=CNA |accessdate=25 February 2020 |date=25 February 2020}}</ref>\n* The fourth death associated with [[Diamond Princess (ship)|''Diamond Princess'']] was confirmed.<ref>{{cite web |title=Fourth passenger from cruise ship dies in Japan: Reports |url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asia/covid-19-coronavirus-japan-diamond-princess-cruise-death-12467980 |website=CNA |accessdate=25 February 2020 |date=25 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== 26 February ===\n'''WHO''' Situation Report 37:<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/situation-reports/20200226-sitrep-37-covid-19.pdf?sfvr