 |publisher=Bahrian MOH |accessdate=26 February 2020}}</ref>\n* Canada confirmed a new case in Toronto of a woman with travel history to Iran. This took the country's total to 12.<ref>{{cite web |title=Ontario confirms new case of coronavirus, patient had travelled to Iran |url=https://nationalpost.com/pmn/news-pmn/canada-news-pmn/ontario-confirms-new-case-of-coronovirus-patient-had-travelled-to-iran |publisher=National Post |accessdate=26 February 2020 |date=26 February 2020}}</ref>\n* Croatia confirmed its second and third cases, the second being the twin brother of the first patient<ref>{{cite web |title=Majka zara\u017eene bra\u0107e radi u ministarstvu: 'Nije bila na poslu i nema dodatnih mjera' |url=https://www.vecernji.hr/vijesti/cekaju-se-nalazi-djevojke-zarazenog-beros-i-ona-pokazuje-znakove-1381776 |publisher=VL |accessdate=26 February 2020}}</ref> and the third being a man who works in Parma, Italy.<ref>{{cite web |title=Potvr\u0111en tre\u0107i slu\u010daj zaraze koronavirusom u Hrvatskoj |url=http://hr.n1info.com/Vijesti/a486325/Potvrdjen-treci-slucaj-zaraze-koronavirusom-u-Hrvatskoj-pacijent-je-u-KBC-Rijeka.html |publisher=N1 |accessdate=26 February 2020}}</ref>\n* Finland reported its second case.<ref>{{cite web |title=Woman in Helsinki tests positive for novel coronavirus |url=https://yle.fi/uutiset/osasto/news/woman_in_helsinki_tests_positive_for_novel_coronavirus/11229433 |publisher=Yle.fi |accessdate=26 February 2020 |date=26 February 2020}}</ref>\n* France confirmed three new cases, taking it to 17 cases. It also announced its second death from the disease, a 60-year-old French man who had been diagnosed the night before.<ref>{{cite web |title=Second person dies from coronavirus in France: Health official |date=25 February 2020 |url=https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/world/2020/02/26/Second-person-dies-from-coronavirus-in-France-Health-official.html |publisher=Al Arabiya |accessdate=26 February 2020}}</ref> An eighteenth case was later declared.<ref>{{cite web |title=Coronavirus: un nouveau cas confirm\u00e9 en France, la femme d'un patient hospitalis\u00e9 \u00e0 Annecy |url=https://www.bfmtv.com/sante/coronavirus-un-nouveau-cas-confirme-en-france-chez-la-femme-d-un-patient-hospitalise-a-annecy-1864859.html |publisher=BFM.TV |accessdate=26 February 2020}}</ref>\n* Georgia reported its first case in the country, a Georgian native travelling from Iran.<ref>{{cite web |title=Georgia reports first coronavirus case in the country: health minister |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-georgia/georgia-reports-first-coronavirus-case-in-the-country-health-minister-idUSKCN20K2SY |publisher=Reuters |accessdate=26 February 2020 |date=26 February 2020}}</ref>\n* Germany reported five additional cases.<ref>{{cite web |title=Germany is at start of coronavirus epidemic: health minister |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-coronavirus-germany/germany-is-at-start-of-coronavirus-epidemic-health-minister |publisher=Reuters |accessdate=26 February 2020}}</ref> By the end of the day the overall total number of cases in the country had risen to 27.<ref>{{cite web |title=COVID-19 updates: Germany facing a 'coronavirus epidemic' |url=https://www.dw.com/en/covid-19-updates-germany-facing-a-coronavirus-epidemic/a-52536472 |publisher=DW.com |accessdate=26 February 2020}}</ref>\n* Greece confirmed its first case, a 38-year-old woman who had recently travelled to Italy.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-greece-idUSKCN20K1IA|title=Greece confirms first coronavirus case|date=26 February 2020|work=Reuters|access-date=26 February 2020|language=en}}</ref>\n* Hong Kong reported six new cases, including a 16-year-old boy and his 21-year-old sister who were both aboard ''Diamond Princess'', bringing the total to 91 cases.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.scmp.com/news/hong-kong/health-environment/article/3052452/coronavirus-six-more-test-positive-hong-kong |title = Boy, 16, among six new confirmed coronavirus cases in Hong Kong|date = 26 February 2020}}</ref>\n* Italy confirmed 51 additional cases, bringing its total to 374. It also confirmed the twelfth death from the virus.<ref>{{cite web |title=Coronavirus, 374 contagiati in Italia, 12 vittime: la prima in Emilia-Romagna. LIVE (in Italian) |url=https://tg24.sky.it/cronaca/2020/02/26/coronavirus-ultime-notizie-diretta.html?intcmp=hp-tg24_hero_main-title_null |website=Sky TG24 |accessdate=26 February 2020 |date=26 February 2020}}</ref> In the evening they declared 27 new cases<ref>{{cite web |title=Coronavirus in Italia: aggiornamento ora per ora |url=https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/22/news/coronavirus_in_italia_aggiornamento_ora_per_ora-249241616/ |publisher=la Repubblica |accessdate=26 February 2020|date=22 February 2020 }}</ref> followed by an additional 54 cases, with two earlier cases declared false positives.<ref>{{cite web |title=LIVE - CORONAVIRUS: SALGONO A 16 I CASI IN LIGURIA |url=https://www.regione.liguria.it/eventi-live/coronavirus-26-febbraio-2020.html |publisher=Region Liguria |accessdate=26 February 2020}}</ref>\n* Iran confirmed four more deaths, taking the total to 19. Another 44 cases were confirmed, bringing the total number to 139.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Gambrell |first1=Jon  |title=Iran raises its death toll to 19 amid 139 coronavirus cases |url=https://apnews.com/5624a77cb07914824586ff7bfe611464 |website=Associated Press |accessdate=26 February 2020 |date=26 February 2020}}</ref>\n* Japan confirmed its second death from the virus.<ref name=\"Japan2Deaths\">{{cite web |title=Japan reports second COVID-19 death, PM urges two-week curbs on sports events |url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asia/japan-reports-second-covid-19-death-pm-urges-two-week-curbs-on-12471074 |website=CNA |accessdate=26 February 2020 |date=26 February 2020}}</ref> It also reported 5 new confirmed cases in Nagoya. A third death was later confirmed.<ref>{{cite web |title=Two elderly in Japan dies after catching COVID-19 |url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asia/covid19-man-japan-dies-coronavirus-third-death-12472926 |website=CNA |accessdate=27 February 2020 |date=26 February 2020}}</ref>\n* Kuwait confirmed that their total of confirmed cases had risen to 12 with one new case. Later that day they confirmed the overall total had risen to 25.<ref>{{cite web |title=New coronavirus cases in Kuwait associated with Iran travel bring total to 25 |url=https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/gulf/2020/02/26/Additional-Iran-traveler-tests-positive-for-coronavirus-in-Kuwait-total-now-12-.html |publisher=Al Arabiya |accessdate=26 February 2020 |date=26 February 2020}}</ref>\n* Lebanon confirmed its second case.<ref>{{cite web |title=Second coronavirus case in Lebanon: Health ministry |date=25 February 2020 |url=https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/02/26/Second-coronavirus-case-in-Lebanon-Health-ministry.html |publisher=Al Arabiya |accessdate=26 February 2020}}</ref>\n* North Macedonia confirmed its first case, a woman who had recently returned home from Italy.<ref>{{cite web  |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-north-macedonia/north-macedonia-confirms-first-case-of-coronavirus|title=Oficial: Primul rom\u00e2n confirmat cu coronavirus |publisher=Reuters |accessdate=26 February 2020}}</ref>\n* Norway confirmed its first case, a person who had returned from China.<ref>{{cite news |title=Norway detects its first case of coronavirus |date=26 February 2020 |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-norway/norway-detects-its-first-case-of-coronavirus-idUSKCN20K31G |agency=Reuters |accessdate=26 February 2020}}</ref>\n* Pakistan confirmed its first case, a 22-year-old man from Sindh province who had travelled to Iran, and also confirmed a second case with no further details.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Ali |first1=Imtiaz |title=Pakistan confirms first two cases of coronavirus, govt says 'no need to panic' |date=26 Februa