wannews.com.tw/en/news/3881582 |website=Taiwan News |accessdate=26 February 2020 |date=26 February 2020}}</ref>\n* Thailand confirmed three additional cases, bringing its total to 40 cases.<ref>{{cite web |title=Thailand has 3 new coronavirus cases, urges travel disclosure |url=https://www.bangkokpost.com/thailand/general/1866094/thailand-has-3-new-coronavirus-cases-total-now-40 |publisher=Bangkok Post |accessdate=26 February 2020 |date=26 February 2020}}</ref>\n* The United States confirmed three new cases - one being a domestic case in California with no travel history, and the other two being former passengers aboard ''Diamond Princess'' - bringing the total number to 60.<ref>{{cite web |title=Coronavirus fears spread across the world |url=https://edition.cnn.com/asia/live-news/coronavirus-outbreak-02-26-20-intl-hnk/h_6c3eaf66897d90acda95d9cc89434d29 |publisher=CNN |accessdate=26 February 2020}}</ref>\n* ''Diamond Princess'' saw 14 new confirmed cases, taking it to 705 cases aboard the ship. It is estimated that more passengers on the ship could be infected than previously thought.<ref>{{cite web |title=Dozens of passengers allowed off virus-hit Diamond Princess ship have symptoms: Japan minister |url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asia/coronavirus-japan-cruise-ship-diamond-princess-dozens-symptoms-12471592 |website=CNA |accessdate=26 February 2020 |date=26 February 2020}}</ref>\n* For the first time, a case was re-imported back to China from another country; the patient travelled from Iran.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.stnn.cc/pcarticle/720355| title=\u4f0a\u6717\u2192\u4fc4\u7f57\u65af\u2192\u4e0a\u6d77\u2192\u5b81\u590f,\u6025\u627e\u8fd9\u4f4d\u786e\u8bca\u60a3\u8005\u63a5\u89e6\u8005}}</ref>\n\n=== 27 February ===\n'''WHO''' Situation Report 38:<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/situation-reports/20200227-sitrep-38-covid-19.pdf?sfvrsn=9f98940c_2|title=Situation Report 38|last=|first=|date=|website=World Health Organization|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n* Austria reported its third case, the first in Vienna.<ref>{{cite web |title=Coronavirus erreicht Wien: 72-J\u00e4hriger erkrankt |url=https://kurier.at/chronik/wien/coronavirus-erreicht-wien-72-jaehriger-erkrankt/400765893 |publisher=Kurier |accessdate=27 February 2020}}</ref>\n* Canada confirmed the first human-to-human transmission in Toronto, the husband of the woman who had travelled to Iran, bringing the total cases in the country to 13.<ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/toronto/ontario-covid-19-coronavirus-iran-husband-1.5477831| title=Husband of Ontario's 5th COVID-19 case also tests positive for coronavirus| website=cbc.ca| date=27 February 2020}}</ref> The country later reported a presumptive case in Quebec. The patient had travel history to Iran. This presumptive case was the first case in Quebec, bringing the total number to 14.<ref>{{cite web |title=Quebec's first presumptive case of coronavirus detected, health minister says |url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/montreal/covid-19-montreal-quebec-1.5479106 |publisher=CBC |accessdate=28 February 2020 |date=28 February 2020}}</ref>\n* China reported through the National Health Commission 433 new cases and 29 new deaths across the mainland. Of those, 409 cases and 26 deaths were in Hubei province.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u622a\u81f32\u670826\u65e524\u65f6\u65b0\u578b\u51a0\u72b6\u75c5\u6bd2\u80ba\u708e\u75ab\u60c5\u6700\u65b0\u60c5\u51b5 |url=http://www.nhc.gov.cn/yjb/s7860/202002/369fb309eded45abaf10645a9c8ceb40.shtml |publisher=China National Health Commission |accessdate=27 February 2020}}</ref>\n* Denmark confirmed its first case, a person who had recently returned from Italy.<ref>{{cite web |title=Dansker smittet med coronavirus |url=https://nyheder.tv2.dk/samfund/2020-02-27-dansker-smittet-med-coronavirus |website=tv2.dk |accessdate=27 February 2020 |date=27 February 2020}}</ref>\n* Estonia reported its first case, an Iranian man who had recently returned from Iran.<ref>{{cite web |title=Eestis leiti esimene koroonaviirusesse nakatunu |url=https://www.err.ee/1057192/eestis-leiti-esimene-koroonaviirusesse-nakatunu |publisher=EESTI |accessdate=27 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Iranian citizen tests positive for coronavirus in Estonia: Ifax |url=https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/world/2020/02/27/Iranian-citizen-tests-positive-for-coronavirus-in-Estonia-TASS.html |publisher=Al Arabiya |accessdate=27 February 2020}}</ref>\n* France reported 20 new cases, raising the number of cases in the country to 38.<ref>{{cite web |title=Coronavirus: le nombre de cas de contamination confirm\u00e9s en France passe de 18 \u00e0 38 |url=https://www.bfmtv.com/sante/direct-coronavirus-covid-19-france-mort-cas-creil-oise-paris-amiens-strasbourg-italie-chine-symptomes-virus-maladie-epidemie |publisher=BFM.TV |accessdate=27 February 2020}}</ref>\n* Germany saw another case reported in North Rhine-Westphalia.<ref>{{cite web |title=Corona-Virus: Suche nach weiteren Infizierten |url=https://www1.wdr.de/nachrichten/themen/coronavirus/corona-infektionen-nrw-100.html |publisher=WDR |accessdate=27 February 2020}}</ref> In the evening it was reported that there were 14 new cases in the same state, bringing Germany's total to 40 cases.<ref>{{cite web |title=NRW meldet 14 neue Infektionen |url=https://www.n-tv.de/panorama/19-17-NRW-meldet-14-neue-Infektionen--article21602064.html |publisher=ntv |accessdate=27 February 2020}}</ref>  The cases rose to 45 by the end of the day.\n* Greece confirmed two more cases, the first patient's daughter and another woman in Athens, bringing the total to 3 cases.<ref name=\":4\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-greece-idUSKCN20L1F3|title=Greece reports two new coronavirus cases, cancels carnival|date=27 February 2020|work=Reuters|access-date=27 February 2020|language=en}}</ref>\n* Hong Kong reported two additional cases, both women infected after visiting a Hong Kong temple at the centre of a COVID-19 cluster. This took the total number of cases to 93.<ref>{{cite web |title=Coronavirus: two more women infected after visiting Hong Kong temple at centre of Covid-19 cluster |url=https://www.scmp.com/news/hong-kong/health-environment/article/3052696/coronavirus-elderly-woman-becomes-hong-kongs-92nd |publisher=South China Morning Posr |accessdate=27 February 2020}}</ref>\n* Iran reported that 22 people had now died amid 141 people infected by the virus.<ref>{{cite web |title=Iran confirms 22 people dead, 141 infected with coronavirus: IRNA |url=https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/02/27/Iran-confirms-22-people-dead-141-infected-with-coronavirus-IRNA-.html |publisher=Al Arabiya |accessdate=27 February 2020}}</ref> The chairman of Iran's National Security Committee, [[Mojtaba Zolnour]], announced he had been infected.<ref>{{cite web |title=Iranian official infected with coronavirus: Fars news agency |url=https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/02/27/Iranian-official-infected-with-coronavirus-Fars-news-agency-.html |publisher=Al Arabiya |accessdate=27 February 2020}}</ref>  Iran later announced an increase to 26 deaths and 245 cases.<ref>{{cite web |title=Iran confirms 26 people dead, 245 infected with coronavirus: Fars |url=https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/02/27/Iran-confirms-22-people-dead-141-infected-with-coronavirus-IRNA-.html |publisher=Al Arabiya |accessdate=27 February 2020}}</ref> The country's Vice President for Women and Family Affairs [[Masoumeh Ebtekar]] also tested positive.<ref>{{cite web |title=Iranian Vice President Masoumeh Ebtekar tests positive for coronavirus: Report |url=https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/02/27/Iranian-Vice-President-Masoumeh-Ebtekar-tests-positive-for-coronavirus-Report.html |publisher=Al Arabiya |accessdate=27 February 2020}}</ref>\n* Iraq reported a new case associated with travelling to Iran, the sixth in the country and the first in Baghdad.<ref>{{cite web |title=Iraq announces sixth coronavirus case associated with travel to Iran |url=https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/02/27/Iraq-announces-new-coronavirus-case-associated-with-travel-to-Iran.html |publisher=Al Arabiya |accessdate=27 February 2020}}</ref> A seventh case was confirmed in Kirkuk later in the day.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rudaw.net/arabic/kurdistan/270220207 |title=\u062a\u0633\u062c\u064a\u0644 \u062d\u0627\u0644\u0629 \u0625\u0635\u0627\u0628\u0629 \u062c\u062f\u064a\u062f\u0629 \u0628\u0641\u064a\u0631\u0648\u0633 \u0643\u0648\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627 \u0641\u064a \u0643\u0631\u0643\u0648\u0643 |publisher=RUDAW |accessdate=27 February 2020}}</ref>\n* Israel reported an additional case, a person who had travelled to Italy, bringing the total number to 3.<ref>{{cite web |title=Israeli who returned from Italy diagnosed with coronavirus: ministry |url=https://www.i24news.tv/en/news/israel/diplomacy-defense/1582799308-israeli-who-returned-from-italy-diagnosed-with-coronavirus-ministry |publisher=i24 news |accessdate=27 February 2020}}</ref>\n* Italy reported that two more people had died, bringing the death toll to 14. The Civil Protection agency reported the number of confirmed cases had risen from 420 to 528.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ansa.it/canale_saluteebenessere/notizie/sanita/2020/02/27/coronavirus_23861224-838b-474b-8ca5-f466910a141e.html|title=Coronavirus, Oms: 'Livello minaccia mondiale virus ora molto alta' - Salute & Benessere|date=22 February 2020|website=ANSA.it}}</ref> Later in the day it was announced that three more people had died, taking the death toll to 17, and the total confirmed cases had risen to 650.<ref>{{cite web |title=Coronavirus death toll in Italy rises to 17 as 650 cases confirmed |url=https://www.thelocal.it/20200227/coronavirus-death-toll-in-italy-rises-to-17-as-650-cases-confirmed |publisher=The Local.it |accessdate=27 February 2020}}</ref> At the end of the day, the total cases rose to 655.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.straight.com/life/1366151/covid-19-canada-nations-13th-case-found-toronto-repatriated-canadians-released|title=COVID-19 in Canada: nation's 13th case found in Toronto as repatriated Canadians released from quarantine|date=27 February 2020|website=The Georgia Straight}}</ref> Mayor Pietro Mazzocchi of [[Borgonovo Val Tidone]] was diagnosed with the virus.<ref>{{cite news|first=Cecile|last=Feuillatre|url=https://www.ctvnews.ca/health/on-the-front-lines-of-coronavirus-with-italy-s-first-sick-mayor-1.4829931|title=On the front lines of coronavirus with Italy's first sick mayor|work=[[CTV News]]|date=27 February 2020|access-date=27 February 2020|archive-url=https://archive.is/FGgX4|archive-date=27 February 2020}}</ref>\n* Japan reported 17 new cases. It confirmed a case involving a recovered patient being reinfected with COVID-19. The total number of local cases had increased to 186.<ref>{{cite web |title=Japanese woman confirmed as COVID-19 case for 2nd time, weeks after initial recovery |url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asia/japan-woman-covid-19-coronavirus-second-time-recovered-12474880 |website=CNA |accessdate=27 February 2020 |date=27 February 2020}}</ref> An eighth person died, a Japanese man in his 80s, who lived in the northern-most island of Hokkaido.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u65b0\u578b\u30b3\u30ed\u30ca\u30a6\u30a4\u30eb\u30b9 80\u4ee3\u7537\u6027\u6b7b\u4ea1 \u5317\u6d77\u9053 \u77e5\u5185\u753a |url=https://www3.nhk.or.jp/news/html/20200227/k10012304391000.html |publisher=NHK |accessdate=27 February 2020}}</ref> Additionally, Prime Minister [[Shinzo Abe]] asked that all elementary, middle, and high schools shall be closed until late March.<ref name=\"Japan to Close Schools Nationwide\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.seattletimes.com/seattle-news/health/japan-to-close-schools-nationwide-to-control-spread-of-virus/ |title=Japan to Close Schools Nationwide |last=Yamaguchi  |first=Mari |date=27 February 2020 |website=The Seattle Times |access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref>\n* Kuwait confirmed the total cases in the country were 43, with all having recently travelled to Iran.<ref>{{cite web |title=Kuwait confirms all 43 coronavirus cases recently traveled to Iran: Health Ministry |url=https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/gulf/2020/02/27/Kuwait-confirms-all-43-coronavirus-cases-recently-traveled-to-Iran-Health-Ministry.html |publisher=Al Arabiya |accessdate=27 February 2020}}</ref>\n* Lebanon reported a third case with the person having travelled from Iran.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u0627\u0644\u0635\u062d\u0629: \u062a\u0633\u062c\u064a\u0644 \u062d\u0627\u0644\u0629 \u0643\u0648\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627 \u062b\u0627\u0644\u062b\u0629 \u0645\u062b\u0628\u062a\u0629 \u0644\u0634\u062e\u0635 \u0625\u064a\u0631\u0627\u0646\u064a \u0623\u062a\u0649 \u0625\u0644\u0649 \u0644\u0628\u0646\u0627\u0646 \u0641\u064a 24/2 (in Arabic) |url=https://www.elnashra.com/news/show/1392132 |publisher=Elnashra |accessdate=27 February 2020}}</ref>\n* Malaysia confirmed an additional case, a woman who had recently travelled to Japan, bringing the total to 23. That made it the first case to be imported from Japan.<ref>{{cite web |title=Latest: A new case positive for COVID19 in Malaysia |url=https://twitter.com/KKMPutrajaya/status/1233013392866066433 |website=Ministry of Health (Malaysia) (retrieved from Twitter) |accessdate=27 February 2020 |date=27 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Coronavirus: Malaysia confirms first case with travel history to Japan |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/asia/se-asia/malaysia-confirms-1st-case-of-coronavirus-with-travel-history-to-japan |website=The Straits Times |accessdate=27 February 2020 |date=27 February 2020}}</ref>\n* The Netherlands reported its first case, a person who had been skiing in Italy.<ref>{{Cite tweet|user=BNODesk|number=1233125330057154565|date=28 February 2020|title=BREAKING: Netherlands reports first case of coronavirus}}</ref> \n* Nigeria confirmed its first case, an Italian citizen who worked in Nigeria and returned from Milan. It was the first case of coronavirus in sub-Saharan Africa.<ref>{{cite web |title=Nigeria confirms first coronavirus case in Sub-Saharan Africa |url=https://www.france24.com/en/20200228-nigeria-coronavirus-milan-italy-pandemic-epidemic-contagion |publisher=France24 |accessdate=28 February 2020|date=28 February 2020 }}</ref>\n* Norway confirmed three additional cases, two in Oslo and one in B\u00e6rum, taking the total to four cases.<ref>{{cite web |title=Coronavirus in Norway: The Latest News on the COVID-19 Outbreak |url=https://www.lifeinnorway.net/coronavirus-in-norway/ |publisher=Life in Norway |accessdate=27 February 2020}}</ref> Two returned from Italy and one from Iran.\n* Oman reported an additional case, raising the country's total to 5.<ref>{{cite web |title=One more coronavirus case reported in Oman |url=https://timesofoman.com/article/2817591/Oman/Health/One-more-coronavirus-case-reported-in-Oman |work=Times of Oman |accessdate=27 February 2020|date=27 February 2020 }}</ref> An additional case was confirmed later that day, who had travelled from Iran.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/OmaniMOH/status/1233080668449624069|title=The #Ministry_of_Health announces the registration of a new novel Corona virus (COVID-19) case, linked to travelling to Iran |website=Twitter |publisher=Oman Ministry of Health |accessdate=27 February 2020}}</ref>\n* San Marino confirmed its first case.<ref>{{cite web |title=Gruppo coordinamento emergenze sanitarie: aggiornamento del 27 febbraio 2020 |url=https://www.sanmarinortv.sm/news/comunicati-c9/gruppo-coordinamento-emergenze-sanitarie-aggiornamento-del-27-febbraio-2020-a184304 |publisher=RTV San Marino |accessdate=27 February 2020|date=27 February 2020 }}</ref>\n* Singapore confirmed three more cases, bringing the total number to 96.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Toh |first1=Ting Wei |last2=Kurohi |first2=Rei |title=Coronavirus: 12-year-old RI student and his family member among 3 new confirmed cases in S'pore; 4 others discharged |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/health/coronavirus-3-new-confirmed-cases-including-one-linked-to-a-previous-case-4 |website=The Straits Times |accessdate=27 February 2020 |date=27 February 2020}}</ref>\n* South Korea reported 334 new cases, bringing the total number to 1,595.<ref>{{cite web |title=S. Korea reports 334 new virus cases, total now at 1,595 |url=https://en.yna.co.kr/view/AEN20200227003900320 |publisher=Yonhap News Agency |accessdate=27 February 2020|date=27 February 2020 }}</ref>  171 additional cases were later confirmed, taking the total number to 1,766.<ref>{{cite web |script-title=ko:[1\ubcf4] \ucf54\ub85c\ub09819 \uc2e0\uaddc\ud658\uc790 171\uba85\u2026\uad6d\ub0b4 \ud655\uc9c4\uc790 \ucd1d 1\ucc9c766\uba85  |language=ko-kr |url=https://www.yna.co.kr/view/AKR20200227182900017 |publisher=.yna.co.kr |accessdate=27 February 2020|date=26 February 2020 }}</ref>\n* Spain saw a new case reported in Valencia<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/GVAsanitat/status/1232939245830115338|title=@GVAsanitat confirma un segundo caso de #coronavirus en la Comunitat Valenciana. Se trata del caso en estudio de un hombre en el @GVAclinic, en Valencia, con s\u00edntomas compatibles con la enfermedad. Los primeros an\u00e1lisis han confirmado la presencia del virus|first=G. V. A.|last=Sanitat|date=27 February 2020}}</ref> and two more in Madrid.<ref>{{cite web |title=Coronavirus, \u00faltimas noticias en directo: Dos nuevos casos positivos en Madrid suben la cifra a catorce |url=https://www.abc.es/sociedad/abci-coronavirus-ultimas-noticias-directo-ascienden-once-casos-positivos-espana-202002270840_directo.html |publisher=ABC Sociedad |accessdate=27 February 2020}}</ref> A further case was reported in Barcelona.<ref>{{cite web |title=Tercer cas importat lleu de coronavirus a Catalunya |url=http://salutweb.gencat.cat/ca/inici/nota-premsa/?id=383472 |publisher=Departament de Salut |accessdate=27 February 2020}}</ref> By the early evening, the total number of confirmed cases had risen to 22.<ref>{{cite web |title=Coronavirus Directo {{!}} Un nuevo positivo de coronavirus en Segovia y seis m\u00e1s en Valencia elevan a 22 los casos activos en Espa\u00f1a |url=https://www.n-tv.de/panorama/19-17-NRW-meldet-14-neue-Infektionen--article21602064.html |publisher=rtve |accessdate=27 February 2020}}</ref> In the evening six additional cases were declared in Valencia.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/GVAsanitat/status/1233094268698361857|title=@GVAsanitat confirma 6 nuevos casos de #coronavirus en la Comunitat Valenciana, lo que suma un total de 8. La consellera @anabarcelochico ha explicado que todos los afectados tienen s\u00edntomas leves y la confirmaci\u00f3n de estos casos indica que las v\u00edas de detecci\u00f3n funcionanpic.twitter.com/JoWrbAISjI|first=G. V. A.|last=Sanitat|date=27 February 2020}}</ref>\n* Sweden had five new cases confirmed, one in the Uppsala region,<ref>{{cite web |title=Flera nya coronafall i Sverige |url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/lokalt/uppsala/forsta-bekraftade-coronafall-i-uppsala |publisher=SVT Nyheter |accessdate=27 February 2020|date=27 February 2020 }}</ref> three people in V\u00e4stra G\u00f6taland, and one in the Stockholm region.<ref>{{cite web |title=Inbjudan till presstr\u00e4ff: Ytterligare fall av covid-19 i flera regioner |url=https://www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se/nyheter-och-press/nyhetsarkiv/2020/februari/inbjudan-till-presstraff-ytterligare-fall-av-covid-19-i-flera-regioner2/ |publisher=Folkhalsomyndigheten |accessdate=27 February 2020}}</ref>\n* Switzerland reported more cases, with a total of six confirmed cases across five cantons.<ref>{{cite web |title=Switzerland confirms sixth coronavirus case |url=https://www.swissinfo.ch/eng/politics/covid-19_switzerland-confirms-second-coronavirus-case/45582788 |publisher=swissinfo.ch |accessdate=27 February 2020}}</ref>  By the end of the day, a total of eight cases had been detected.\n* The United Arab Emirates reported the recovery of two patients, and six new cases, bringing the total number to 19.<ref>{{cite web |title=UAE confirms recovery of two coronavirus patients, registers six new cases |url=https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/gulf/2020/02/27/UAE-confirms-recovery-of-two-coronavirus-patients-registers-six-new-cases.html |publisher=Al Arabiya |accessdate=27 February 2020}}</ref> It also saw two suspected cases attached to the UAE Tour, a cycling event, which resulted in the cancellation of the event.<ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus outbreak: UAE Tour cancelled due to two 'suspected' cases |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/cycling/51667939 |accessdate=28 February 2020|work=BBC Sport |date=28 February 2020 }}</ref>\n* The United Kingdom confirmed two more cases, contracted in Italy and Tenerife, taking the total to 15 cases.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.gov.uk/government/news/cmo-for-england-announces-2-new-cases-of-novel-coronavirus |title=CMO for England announces 2 new cases of novel coronavirus |publisher=gov.uk |accessdate=27 February 2020}}</ref> In the evening, a sixteenth case was confirmed, and the first case in Northern Ireland, someone who had come from Italy via Dublin.<ref>{{cite news |title=Northern Ireland diagnoses first coronavirus case |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-51667483 |accessdate=27 February 2020|work=BBC News |date=27 February 2020 }}</ref>\n\n=== 28 February ===\n[[File:Communiqu\u00e9 de presse du Conseil f\u00e9d\u00e9ral, 28.02.2020 (cropped).jpg|thumb|Press release of the [[Federal Council (Switzerland)|Swiss government]] banning events of more than 1,000 people (28 February 2020).]]\n\n'''WHO''' Situation Report 39:<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/situation-reports/20200228-sitrep-39-covid-19.pdf?sfvrsn=aa1b80a7_2|title=Situation 