elocal.dk/20200228/second-danish-coronavirus-infection-identified |website=The Local Denmark |accessdate=28 February 2020 |date=28 February 2020}}</ref>\n* Finland confirmed an additional case, taking it to 3 confirmed cases.<ref>{{cite web |title=3rd case of coronavirus infection spotted in Finland |url=http://www.dailyfinland.fi/health/14589/3rd-case-of-coronavirus-infection-spotted-in-Finland |publisher=Daily Finland |accessdate=28 February 2020 |date=28 February 2020}}</ref>\n* France announced two new cases, bringing the total number to 40.<ref>{{cite web |title=Coronavirus: le maire de La Balme-de-Sillingy, en Haute-Savoie, annonce 2 nouveaux cas |url=https://www.bfmtv.com/societe/coronavirus-le-maire-de-la-balme-de-sillingy-en-haute-savoie-annonce-2-nouveaux-cas-1865847.html |publisher=BFM |accessdate=28 February 2020 |date=28 February 2020}}</ref>  The total number of cases later rose to 57.\n* Georgia confirmed a second case, a citizen who had returned from Italy. More than 18 people were reported to be in quarantine.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u10e1\u10d0\u10e5\u10d0\u10e0\u10d7\u10d5\u10d4\u10da\u10dd\u10e8\u10d8 \u10d0\u10ee\u10d0\u10da\u10d8 \u10d9\u10dd\u10e0\u10dd\u10dc\u10d0\u10d5\u10d8\u10e0\u10e3\u10e1\u10d8\u10e1 \u10de\u10d8\u10e0\u10d5\u10d4\u10da\u10d8 \u10e8\u10d4\u10db\u10d7\u10ee\u10d5\u10d4\u10d5\u10d0 \u10d3\u10d0\u10e4\u10d8\u10e5\u10e1\u10d8\u10e0\u10d3\u10d0 (in Georgian) |url=http://www.ghn.ge/news/240287-sakartveloshi-koronavirusis-pirveli-shemtkhveva-dafiksirda |publisher=Georgian News Agency |accessdate=28 February 2020 |date=28 February 2020}}</ref>\n* Germany reported cases totalling \"almost 60\", according to a Health Ministry official.<ref>{{cite web |title=Almost 60 reported cases of coronavirus in Germany: Health ministry |url=https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/world/2020/02/28/Almost-60-reported-cases-of-coronavirus-in-Germany-Health-ministry-.html |publisher=Al Arabiya |accessdate=28 February 2020 |date=28 February 2020}}</r