f>\n* Croatia confirmed its sixth case, a close relative of the third and fifth patients.<ref>{{cite web |title=Potvr\u0111en \u0161esti slu\u010daj koronavirusa u Hrvatskoj (in Croatian) |url=https://www.index.hr/vijesti/clanak/potvrdjen-sesti-slucaj-koronavirusa-u-hrvatskoj-radi-se-o-muskarcu-iz-rijeke/2160942.aspx |publisher=Index.hr |accessdate=28 February 2020}}</ref>\n* Denmark confirmed its third case, a person recently returned from a trip to Munich, Germany, where he came into contact with someone who was later determined to have the virus.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Ahrens|first=Kevin|last2=Ingvorsen|first2=Emil S\u00f8nderg\u00e5rd|url=https://www.dr.dk/nyheder/indland/tredje-dansker-smitttet-med-coronavirus|title=Tredje dansker smitttet med coronavirus|date=29 February 2020|work=DR|access-date=29 February 2020|url-status=live|language=da|trans-title=Third Dane infected with coronavirus}}</ref>\n* Ecuador confirmed its first case, a woman who recently returned from a trip to Spain.<ref>{{cite web |title=Ecuador confirm\u00f3 el primer caso de coronavirus (in Spanish) |url=https://www.infobae.com/america/america-latina/2020/02/29/ecuador-confirmo-el-primer-caso-de-coronavirus/ |publisher=Infobae |accessdate= 29 February 2020}}</ref>\n* France confirmed 16 additional cases, bringing the total number to 73.<ref name=\"CNAFrance29Feb\">{{cite web |title=France bans gatherings of more than 5,000 people after COVID-19 cases rise to 73 |url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/world/france-bans-gatherings-5000-people-covid-19-cases-rise-12485940 |website=CNA |accessdate=29 February 2020 |date=29 February 2020}}</ref> Additional cases were confirmed, taking the number to 100.<ref>{{cite web |title=Coronavirus: la barre des 100 cas atteinte en France, un premier mort aux \u00c9tats-Unis (in French) |url=https://www.bfmtv.com/sante/sante-publique/en-direct-coronavirus-pres-de-600-supplementaires-et-16-morts-en-coree-du-sud/ |website=BFM TV |accessdate=29 February 2020 |d