nal Development and Reform Commission]] (NDRC) issued an additional \u00a5200 million (US$28.66 million) for Hubei to improve the treatment capacity of patients with severe infections.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jiemian.com/article/3958370.html|language=zh-Hans |script-title=zh:\u56fd\u5bb6\u53d1\u6539\u59d4\u7d27\u6025\u4e0b\u8fbe2\u4ebf\u5143\u652f\u6301\u6e56\u5317\u63d0\u9ad8\u91cd\u75c7\u611f\u67d3\u60a3\u8005\u6551\u6cbb\u80fd\u529b{{!}}\u754c\u9762\u65b0\u95fb \u00b7 \u5feb\u8baf|website=www.jiemian.com|access-date=8 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n[[Leishenshan Hospital]] begins operation.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jiemian.com/article/3959045.html |language=zh-cn |script-title=zh:\u96f7\u795e\u5c71\u533b\u96621600\u5f20\u75c5\u5e8a\u4eca\u5929\u5c06\u4ea4\u4ed8\u4f7f\u7528{{!}}\u754c\u9762\u65b0\u95fb \u00b7 \u5feb\u8baf|website=www.jiemian.com|access-date=8 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe [[National Health Commission]] announces the temporary official names and acronyms for the pneumonia in Chinese and English, respectively {{linktext|lang=zh-Hans|\u65b0\u578b|\u51a0\u72b6\u75c5\u6bd2|\u80ba\u708e}} ({{zh|p=x\u012bnx\u00edng gu\u0101nzhu\u00e0ng b\u00ecngd\u00fa f\u00e8iy\u00e1n}}) / ''Novel Coronavirus Pneumonia'' and {{lang|zh-Hans|\u65b0\u51a0\u80ba\u708e}} ({{zh|links=no|p=x\u012bngu\u0101n f\u00e8iy\u00e1n}}) / ''NCP''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jiemian.com/article/3959263.html|language=zh-Hans |script-title=zh:\u56fd\u5bb6\u536b\u5065\u59d4\uff1a\u5c06\u201c\u65b0\u578b\u51a0\u72b6\u75c5\u6bd2\u611f\u67d3\u7684\u80ba\u708e\u201d\u7684\u7edf\u4e00\u7b80\u79f0\u4e3a\u201c\u65b0\u51a0\u80ba\u708e\u201d{{!}}\u754c\u9762\u65b0\u95fb \u00b7 \u5feb\u8baf|website=www.jiemian.com|access-date=8 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== 10 February ===\nBusiness has now resumed in all 30 mainland province-level divisions, apart from Hubei.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jiemian.com/article/3968076.html |language=zh-cn |script-title=zh:\u590d\u4ea7\u590d\u5de5\u5b89\u5168\u6709\u5e8f\uff0c\u4e0a\u5e02\u516c\u53f8\u5bf9\u672a\u6765\u7ecf\u6d4e\u6709\u4fe1\u5fc3{{!}}\u754c\u9762\u65b0\u95fb \u00b7 \u5feb\u8baf|website=www.jiemian.com|access-date=11 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nFood prices in China have risen on month of January. According to the consumer price index (CPI) the price of pork rose 8.5%, while the CPI came in at 5.4%. The reason may be due to food hoarding, besides the disruptions of supply chains due to transportation, lockdown measures and holiday demand.<ref>{{cite web |title=China inflation rises as coronavirus disrupts supply chains |url=https://www.france24.com/en/20200210-china-inflation-rises-as-coronavirus-disrupts-supply-chains |website=France 24 |publisher=France 24 |accessdate=10 February 2020 |date=10 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=China Inflation Accelerates on Holiday Demand and Outbreak |url=https://business.financialpost.com/pmn/business-pmn/china-inflation-accelerates-on-holiday-demand-virus-outbreak |website=Bloomberg News |publisher=Bloomberg News |accessdate=10 February 2020 |date=10 February 2020}}</ref> The CPI is the highest since October 2011.<ref>{{cite web |title=China's inflation rises amid virus outbreak |url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/international/business/chinas-inflation-rises-amid-virus-outbreak/tough-decisions-for-china/slideshow/74065114.cms |website=The Economist Times |publisher=AFP |accessdate=10 February 2020 |date=10 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n[[Communist Party of China|Chinese Communist Party]] [[General Secretary of the Communist Party of China|general secretary]] [[Xi Jinping]] has appeared in public wearing a protective mask and his temperature was checked while visiting the Anhuali Community in Chaoyang District of Beijing.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Kuo |first1=Lily |title=Xi Jinping appears in public as China returns to work after holiday |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/feb/10/coronavirus-who-warns-spread-by-people-who-had-not-visited-china-could-be-tip-of-the-iceberg |website=The Guardian |accessdate=10 February 2020 |date=10 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author1=Xinhua |title=Xi inspects novel coronavirus prevention, control work in Beijing |url=https://www.globaltimes.cn/content/1179056.shtml |website=Global Times |publisher=Global Times |accessdate=10 February 2020 |date=10 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n[[Tibetan New Year]] public activities due to occur on 24 February were suspended due to the [[Coronavirus disease 2019]] epidemic.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.xinhuanet.com/english/2020-02/10/c_138770377.htm|title=Tibetan New Year activities called off amid virus outbreak - Xinhua {{!}} English.news.cn|website=www.xinhuanet.com|access-date=12 February 2020}}</ref> Praying activities inside monasteries in Lhasa will be held but will be shortened, without the participation of the public and in a smaller scale.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.cgtn.com/news/2020-02-10/Tibetan-New-Year-activities-called-off-due-to-coronavirus-epidemic-NYs0D6EnQc/index.html|title=Tibetan New Year activities called off due to coronavirus epidemic|website=news.cgtn.com|language=en|access-date=12 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== 11 February ===\n[[Shenzhen University]] announced the successful development of a new coronavirus antibody detection kit capable of obtaining a result in 22 minutes and reducing the risk of infection of medical staff.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jiemian.com/article/3970636.html |language=zh-cn |script-title=zh:22\u5206\u949f\u53ef\u83b7\u7ed3\u679c\uff0c\u6df1\u5927\u79f0\u7814\u53d1\u6210\u529f\u65b0\u51a0\u75c5\u6bd2\u6297\u4f53\u68c0\u6d4b\u8bd5\u5242\u76d2{{!}}\u754c\u9762\u65b0\u95fb \u00b7 \u5feb\u8baf|website=www.jiemian.com|access-date=11 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Ministry of Human Resources and Social Security]] expanded existing relief measures for micro, small, and medium size enterprises.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jiemian.com/article/3969029.html |language=zh-cn |script-title=z