led by Dr. Bruce Aylward and Dr Wannian Liang and consisted of experts from China, Germany, Japan, Korea, Nigeria, Russia, Singapore, USA\u00a0 and WHO started an investigation.<ref name=\":6\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.who.int/publications-detail/report-of-the-who-china-joint-mission-on-coronavirus-disease-2019-(covid-19)|title=Report of the WHO-China Joint Mission on Coronavirus Disease 2019 (COVID-19)|website=www.who.int|language=en|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n\n=== 17 February ===\nFollowing its announcement the previous night, [[Xiaogan]] now bans all its urban residents from leaving home, all its rural residents from wandering, visiting neighbours, and gathering, and all vehicles from roads. Exceptions are made for medical reasons, medical staff, providers of medical and living provision, pregnancies, deaths, essential vehicles, and others granted permissions. Violators would be subject to up to 10 days of detention and put on the dishonest list.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://view.inews.qq.com/a/20200216A0PF3Q00|language=zh |script-title=zh:\u6e56\u5317\u5b5d\u611f\uff1a\u6240\u6709\u57ce\u9547\u5c45\u6c11\u5fc5\u987b\u8db3\u4e0d\u51fa\u6237\uff0c\u8fdd\u8005\u590410\u65e5\u4ee5\u4e0b\u6cbb\u5b89\u62d8\u7559|website=view.inews.qq.com|access-date=16 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nFollowing its announcement on the previous day, Hangzhou resumes normal traffic and public transport service.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://std.stheadline.com/instant/articles/detail/1202384/%E5%8D%B3%E6%99%82-%E4%B8%AD%E5%9C%8B-%E6%9D%AD%E5%B7%9E%E5%9F%8E%E5%B8%82%E5%85%AC%E5%85%B1%E4%BA%A4%E9%80%9A%E5%AE%A2%E9%81%8B%E5%8F%8A%E5%9C%B0%E9%90%B5-%E6%98%8E%E5%87%8C%E6%99%A8%E8%B5%B7%E6%81%A2%E5%BE%A9%E6%9C%8D%E5%8B%99 |language=zh-hk |script-title=zh:\u676d\u5dde\u57ce\u5e02\u516c\u5171\u4ea4\u901a\u5ba2\u904b\u53ca\u5730\u9435 \u660e\u51cc\u6668\u8d77\u6062\u5fa9\u670d\u52d9|last=\u661f\u5cf6\u65e5\u5831|website=std.stheadline.com |access-date=17 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nA new makeshift hospital was delivered in [[Xi'an]], the capital of [[Shaanxi|Shaanxi Province]]. According to Xinhua, the hospital was designated to treat COVID-19 patients, has 500 beds and 666 medical workers have been dispatched to the hospital.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.xinhuanet.com/english/2020-02/17/c_138791729.htm|title=Makeshift hospital delivered in northwest China city amid coronavirus battle - Xinhua {{!}} English.news.cn|website=www.xinhuanet.com|access-date=17 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn a meeting of the [[Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference]] (CPPCC) it was considered the delaying of the National People's Congress' annual session in March.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.cgtn.com/news/2020-02-17/China-s-top-political-advisory-body-considers-delaying-annual-session--O9Xi5tIGY0/index.html|title=Top political advisory body considers delaying annual session in March|website=news.cgtn.com|language=en|access-date=17 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nFollowing rumors that a researcher named Huang Yanling at The Wuhan Institute of Virology was patient zero, the Institute first denied that there was ever a researcher working there by that name; only after being informed that the researcher's name was still on their Internet page, although her photograph and background were blank, did the Institute acknowledge that a person by that name had worked there, and had since \"left the office,\" current whereabouts unknown. <ref name=\"nationalreview1\">{{cite web|last=Geraghty |first=Jim |url=https://www.nationalreview.com/2020/04/coronavirus-china-trail-leading-back-to-wuhan-labs/ |title=Coronavirus & China: Origin in Wuhan Lab Unproven, But Denials Unconvincing |publisher=National Review |date=2020-04-03 |accessdate=2020-04-09}}</ref>\nSo far, no one knows the whereabouts of Huang Yanling. There are no public denouncements from Huang. However, \"Wei Hongping, a research fellow at the Wuhan Institute of Virology and mentor of Huang, posted on his WeChat Moments that he recently called Huang and confirmed Huang was in good heath\" <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.globaltimes.cn/content/1179675.shtml |title=Wuhan Institute of Virology denies patient zero of COVID-19 came from institute - Global Times |publisher=Globaltimes.cn |date= |accessdate=2020-04-08}}</ref>\n\n=== 18 February ===\nThe State Council introduced exemptions of enterprise social security and housing fund contributions.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://finance.sina.com.cn/roll/2020-02-19/doc-iimxxstf2578980.shtml|language=zh-Hans |script-title=zh:\u56fd\u52a1\u9662\u5927\u62db\u5bf9\u51b2\u75ab\u60c5\uff1a\u4e2d\u5c0f\u5fae\u4f01\u4e1a\u4e09\u9879\u793e\u4fdd\u514d\u5f815\u4e2a\u6708|last=\u65b0\u6d6a\u8d22\u7ecf\u7efc\u5408|date=19 February 2020|website=finance.sina.com.cn|access-date=19 February 2020}}</ref> The [[State Taxation Administration]] (STA) extended the February taxation filing deadline outside Hubei to 28 February.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jiemian.com/article/3997401.html|language=zh-Hans |script-title=zh:\u56fd\u5bb6\u7a0e\u52a1\u603b\u5c40\u53d1\u5e03\u8fdb\u4e00\u6b65\u5ef6\u957f2020\u5e742\u6708\u4efd\u7eb3\u7a0e\u7533\u62a5\u671f\u9650\u6709\u5173\u4e8b\u9879\u7684\u901a\u77e5{{!}}\u754c\u9762\u65b0\u95fb \u00b7 \u5feb\u8baf|website=www.jiemian.com|access-date=19 February 2020}}</ref> The [[State Council of the People's Republic of China|State Council]] and [[Ministry of Finance of the People's Republic of China|Ministry of Finance]] (MoF) announced allocating more budget this year to areas heavily affected by the epidemic.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jiemian.com/article/3997688.html|language=zh-Hans |script-title=zh:\u56fd\u52a1\u9662\u6276\u8d2b\u529e\u3001\u8d22\u653f\u90e8\uff1a\u65b0\u589e\u8d44\u91d1\u5206\u914d\u6d4b\u7b97\u65f6\u5411\u53d7\u75ab\u60c5\u5f71\u54cd\u8f83\u91cd\u5730\u533a\u9002\u5f53\u503e\u659c{{!}}\u754c\u9762\u65b0\u95fb \u00b7 \u5feb\u8baf|website=www.jiemian.com|access-date=19 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nWuhan passes its strictest control measures.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jiemian.com/article/3997244.html|language=zh-Hans |script-title=zh:\u6b66\u6c49\u91c7\u53d6\u6700\u4e25\u683c\u9632\u75ab\u63aa\u65bd\uff1a\u6b66\u6c49\u89c4\u5b9a\u4e0d\u670d\u4ece\u75ab\u60c5\u7ba1\u63a7\u53ef\u91c7\u53d6\u5f3a\u5236\u63aa\u65bd{{!}}\u754c\u9762\u65b0\u95fb \u00b7 \u5feb\u8baf|website=www.jiemian.com|access-date=19 February 2020}}</ref> Tianjin now requires QR code scanning for entering public spaces and transport services.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jiemian.com/article/3997117.html |language=zh-cn |script-title=zh:\u5929\u6d25\uff1a17\u65e5\u8d77\u51fa\u5165\u516c\u5171\u573a\u3001\u4e58\u5750\u516c\u5171\u4ea4\u901a\u5de5\u5177\uff0c\u5fc5\u987b\u626b\u7801\u767b\u8bb0{{!}}\u754c\u9762\u65b0\u95fb \u00b7 \u5feb\u8baf|website=www.jiemian.com|access-date=19 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n[[Yiwu International Trade City]] reopened for business.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://jinhua.zjol.com.cn/jsbd/202002/t20200218_11684672.shtml |language=zh-cn |script-title=zh:\u5168\u7403\u6700\u5927\u5c0f\u5546\u54c1\u5e02\u573a\u4eca\u5929\u5f00\u5e02\uff1a\u4e00\u4eba\u4e00\u7801\u6d4b\u4f53\u6e29 \u590d\u5de5\u8fd8\u6709\u5927\u793c\u5305\u6d59\u6c5f\u5728\u7ebf\u91d1\u534e\u9891\u9053|website=jinhua.zjol.com.cn|access-date=19 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nShanghai requires educational institutions to conduct online education when the new semester starts on 2 March, so that student will not go to school.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jiemian.com/article/3999134.html |language=zh-cn |script-title=zh:3\u6708\u4efd\u8d77\uff0c\u4e0a\u6d77\u5927\u4e2d\u5c0f\u5b66\u5c06\u5f00\u5c55\u5728\u7ebf\u6559\u80b2{{!}}\u754c\u9762\u65b0\u95fb \u00b7 \u5feb\u8baf|website=www.jiemian.com|access-date=19 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== 19 February ===\nThe [[National Health Commission|NHC]] published the sixth pilot version of Diagnostic and Treatment Plan of the Novel Coronavirus Pneumonia,<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.nhc.gov.cn/yzygj/s7653p/202002/8334a8326dd94d329df351d7da8aefc2.shtml |language=zh-cn |script-title=zh:\u5173\u4e8e\u5370\u53d1\u65b0\u578b\u51a0\u72b6\u75c5\u6bd2\u80ba\u708e\u8bca\u7597\u65b9\u6848\uff08\u8bd5\u884c\u7b2c\u516d\u7248\uff09\u7684\u901a\u77e5 |last= |first= |date= |website= |url-status=live |archive-url= |archive-date= |access-date= }}{{Dead link|date=April 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> which removed the category of clinical diagnosis introduced in the previous edition for Hubei, as well as adjusted several descriptions, criteria, and treatment guidelines of COVID-19,.\n\nFollowing its announcement on the previous day, Zhejiang now requires declaration for vehicles entering the province.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jiemian.com/article/4001322.html |language=zh-cn |script-title=zh:\u6d59\u6c5f\uff1a19\u65e50\u65f6\u8d77\u81ea\u9a7e\u8fd4\u6d59\u6216\u9014\u7ecf\u8f66\u8f86\u5747\u9700\u201c\u5165\u6d59\u901a\u884c\u7533\u62a5\u201d{{!}}\u754c\u9762\u65b0\u95fb \u00b7 \u5feb\u8baf|website=www.jiemian.com|access-date=19 February 2020}}</ref> Meanwhile, public transport across the province apart from Wenzhou will now resume normal service.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.guancha.cn/politics/2020_02_18_536964.shtml |language=zh-cn |script-title=zh:\u4eca\u5929\u8d77\uff0c\u9664\u6e29\u5dde\u5916\uff0c\u6d59\u6c5f\u5404\u8bbe\u533a\u5e02\u5e02\u672c\u7ea7\u8981\u5168\u9762\u6062\u590d\u516c\u5171\u4ea4\u901a\u8fd0\u8425|website=www.guancha.cn|access-date=19 February 2020}}</ref> Guangdong resumes inter-provincial busses in response to the travel needs of migrant workers.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.gd.xinhuanet.com/newscenter/2020-02/19/c_1125595349.htm |language=zh-cn |script-title=zh:\u5e7f\u4e1c\u6062\u590d\u519c\u6c11\u5de5\u8f93\u51fa\u5927\u7701\u95f4\u7701\u9645\u5305\u8f66\u548c\u73ed\u8f66\u8fd0\u8425|date=19 February 2020|website=www.xinhuanet.com}}</ref>\n\nWuhan bans all vehicles from roads apart from essential vehicles.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jiemian.com/article/4004921.html|language=zh-Hans |script-title=zh:\u6b66\u6c49\u673a\u52a8\u8f66\u7ba1\u63a7\u65b0\u653f\uff1a\u9664\u6297\u75ab\u548c\u7279\u6b8a\u7528\u9014\u5916\u8f66\u8f86\u4e00\u5f8b\u7981\u884c{{!}}\u754c\u9762\u65b0\u95fb \u00b7 \u5feb\u8baf|website=www.jiemian.com|access-date=19 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nHunan introduced measures to support businesses.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jiemian.com/article/4004083.html|language=zh |script-title=zh:\u6e56\u5357\u51fa\u53f0\u4e09\u5341\u6761\u653f\u7b56\u652f\u6301\u4f01\u4e1a\u5171\u6e21\u96be\u5173\uff0c\u6d89\u91d1\u878d\u3001\u793e\u4fdd\u3001\u7a0e\u8d39\u7b49{{!}}\u754c\u9762\u65b0\u95fb \u00b7 \u5feb\u8baf|website=www.jiemian.com|access-date=19 February 2020}}</ref> Chengdu adjusted its epidemic control procedures and business resumption would no longer require approval.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jiemian.com/article/4004885.html |language=zh-cn |script-title=zh:\u6210\u90fd\u8c03\u6574\u9632\u63a7\u63aa\u65bd\uff1a\u4f01\u4e1a\u590d\u5de5\u65e0\u9700\u5ba1\u6279{{!}}\u754c\u9762\u65b0\u95fb \u00b7 \u5feb\u8baf|website=www.jiemian.com|access-date=19 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== 20 February ===\nHubei requires businesses in the province not to resume before 10 March, except for essential industries.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nbd.com.cn/articles/2020-02-20/1409863.html|language=zh |script-title=zh:\u6e56\u5317\u7701\u5185\u4f01\u4e1a\u5148\u6309\u4e0d\u65e9\u4e8e3\u670810\u65e524\u65f6\u524d\u590d\u5de5 \u5b66\u6821\u5ef6\u671f\u5f00\u5b66|last=|first=|date=20 February 2020|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=20 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nWenzhou removed all checkpoints except in [[Yueqing]] and reopened highways.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jiemian.com/article/4010536.html |language=zh-cn |script-title=zh:\u6e29\u5dde\u64a4\u9500\u5e02\u57df\u8303\u56f4\u6709\u5173\u68c0\u67e5\u5361\u70b9{{!}}\u754c\u9762\u65b0\u95fb \u00b7 \u5feb\