thout the proper authorisation. Several officials behind the order were reprimanded as a result.<ref>{{cite web |title=Coronavirus epicentre Wuhan revokes announcement easing lockdown |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/asia/east-asia/coronavirus-epicentre-wuhan-revokes-announcement-easing-lockdown |website=The Straits Times |accessdate=24 February 2020 |date=24 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nYunnan adjusted its emergency response level from level 1 to level 3,<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.jiemian.com/article/4020423.html|title=\u4e91\u5357\u5e94\u6025\u54cd\u5e94\u8c03\u6574\u4e3a\u4e09\u7ea7{{!}}\u754c\u9762\u65b0\u95fb \u00b7 \u5feb\u8baf|work=www.jiemian.com|accessdate=28 February 2020}}</ref> and Guangdong and Jiangsu to level 2.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.jiemian.com/article/4020555.html|title=\u5e7f\u4e1c\u7701\u51b3\u5b9a\u7701\u91cd\u5927\u7a81\u53d1\u516c\u5171\u536b\u751f\u4e8b\u4ef6\u4e00\u7ea7\u54cd\u5e94\u8c03\u6574\u4e3a\u4e8c\u7ea7\u54cd\u5e94{{!}}\u754c\u9762\u65b0\u95fb \u00b7 \u5feb\u8baf|work=www.jiemian.com|accessdate=28 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jiemian.com/article/4025047.html|title=\u6c5f\u82cf\u5c06\u75ab\u60c5\u9632\u63a7\u4e00\u7ea7\u54cd\u5e94\u8c03\u6574\u4e3a\u4e8c\u7ea7\u54cd\u5e94{{!}}\u754c\u9762\u65b0\u95fb \u00b7 \u5feb\u8baf|website=www.jiemian.com|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref> Jiangxi adjusted its levels to level 3 or level 2 depending on the risk of the county.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jiemian.com/article/4025095.html|title=\u6c5f\u897f\u8c03\u657440\u4e2a\u4f4e\u98ce\u9669\u53bf\uff08\u5e02\u3001\u533a\uff09\u91cd\u5927\u7a81\u53d1\u516c\u5171\u536b\u751f\u4e8b\u4ef6\u5e94\u6025\u54cd\u5e94\u7b49\u7ea7{{!}}\u754c\u9762\u65b0\u95fb \u00b7 \u5feb\u8baf|website=www.jiemian.com|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nDraft legislation was introduced to the Standing Committee of the National People's Congress with a comprehensive ban of the trading and overeating of wildlife.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jiemian.com/article/4021122.html|title=\u5168\u9762\u7981\u6b62\u975e\u6cd5\u91ce\u751f\u52a8\u7269\u4ea4\u6613\u8349\u6848\u63d0\u8bf7\u5168\u56fd\u4eba\u5927\u5e38\u59d4\u4f1a\u5ba1\u8bae{{!}}\u754c\u9762\u65b0\u95fb \u00b7 \u5feb\u8baf|website=www.jiemian.com|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=China 'comprehensively' bans illegal wildlife trade after COVID-19 outbreak |url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asia/coronavirus-covid19-china-ban-wildlife-trade-12464294 |website=CNA |accessdate=27 February 2020 |date=24 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-wildlife-idUSKCN20J069|title=China bans trade, consumption of wild animals due to coronavirus|date=25 February 2020|work=Reuters|access-date=28 February 2020|language=en}}</ref>\n\nThe Third Session of the 13th CPPCC National Committee originally scheduled for 3 March was postponed.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://politics.people.com.cn/n1/2020/0225/c1001-31602359.html|title=\u5168\u56fd\u653f\u534f\u5341\u4e09\u5c4a\u4e09\u6b21\u4f1a\u8bae\u63a8\u8fdf\u53ec\u5f00--\u65f6\u653f--\u4eba\u6c11\u7f51|website=politics.people.com.cn|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== 25 February ===\nIn response the epidemic situation in South Korea and an apparent significant surge of demand for flight tickets from South Korea to Shandong cities, [[Qingdao]] will now quarantine all persons entering with a travel history of areas with the epidemic,<ref>{{cite web |title=\u9752\u5c9b\uff1a\u5bf9\u5165\u5883\u4eba\u5458\u4e2d\u7684\"\u56db\u7c7b\u60c5\u5f62\"\u5b9e\u884c\u96c6\u4e2d\u9694\u79bb\u6216\u7559\u89c2|url=http://www.takungpao.com/news/232108/2020/0225/419743.html|website=Takungpao |accessdate=25 February 2020 |date=25 February 2020}}</ref> [[Weihai]] will now quarantine all persons entering from Japan and South Korea for 14 days,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://finance.eastmoney.com/a/202002251396392719.html|title=\u5a01\u6d77\uff1a\u4eca\u8d77\u4ece\u65e5\u97e9\u7b49\u5165\u5883\u4eba\u5458\u7edf\u4e00\u514d\u8d39\u96c6\u4e2d\u5c45\u4f4f14\u5929|date=25 February 2020}}</ref> [[Shenyang]] will now test the temperature of all passengers entering from the city,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jiemian.com/article/4028517.html|title=\u6c88\u9633\u4e25\u9632\u5883\u5916\u75ab\u60c5\u8f93\u5165{{!}}\u754c\u9762\u65b0\u95fb \u00b7 \u5feb\u8baf|website=www.jiemian.com|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref> and [[Dalian]] will now include all foreigners into its epidemic control mechanism.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jiemian.com/article/4026753.html|title=\u5927\u8fde\u5b9e\u65bd\u5916\u7c4d\u4eba\u5458\u9632\u75ab\u5c5e\u5730\u7ba1\u7406\uff0c\u5bf9\u65e5\u97e9\u9886\u4e8b\u673a\u6784\u901a\u62a5\u4fe1\u606f{{!}}\u754c\u9762\u65b0\u95fb \u00b7 \u5feb\u8baf|website=www.jiemian.com|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe State Council introduced an exemption of the [[Value-added tax|VAT]] of small-scale taxpayers in Hubei for three months,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jiemian.com/article/4028874.html|title=\u56fd\u52a1\u9662\uff1a\u514d\u5f81\u6e56\u5317\u5883\u5185\u5c0f\u89c4\u6a21\u7eb3\u7a0e\u4eba\u589e\u503c\u7a0e3\u4e2a\u6708{{!}}\u754c\u9762\u65b0\u95fb \u00b7 \u5feb\u8baf|website=www.jiemian.com|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref> as well as aid measures for individual businesses<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jiemian.com/article/4028860.html|title=\u674e\u514b\u5f3a\uff1a\u90e8\u7f72\u5bf9\u4e2a\u4f53\u5de5\u5546\u6237\u52a0\u5927\u6276\u6301{{!}}\u754c\u9762\u65b0\u95fb \u00b7 \u5feb\u8baf|website=www.jiemian.com|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref> and stimulus measures for migrant workers and university graduates.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jiemian.com/article/4028846.html|title=\u674e\u514b\u5f3a\uff1a\u63a8\u51fa\u9f13\u52b1\u5438\u7eb3\u9ad8\u6821\u6bd5\u4e1a\u751f\u548c\u519c\u6c11\u5de5\u5c31\u4e1a\u7684\u63aa\u65bd{{!}}\u754c\u9762\u65b0\u95fb \u00b7 \u5feb\u8baf|website=www.jiemian.com|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nInner Mongolia adjusted its emergency response level to level 3.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jiemian.com/article/4029145.html|title=\u5185\u8499\u53e4\u5c06\u91cd\u5927\u7a81\u53d1\u516c\u5171\u536b\u751f\u4e8b\u4ef6\u4e00\u7ea7\u54cd\u5e94\u8c03\u6574\u4e3a\u4e09\u7ea7{{!}}\u754c\u9762\u65b0\u95fb \u00b7 \u5feb\u8baf|website=www.jiemian.com|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nGuangzhou will now test all inpatients for SARS-CoV-19.<ref name=\"auto1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.jiemian.com/article/4029191.html|title=\u4eca\u540e\u5e7f\u5dde\u65b0\u5165\u9662\u60a3\u8005\u5747\u9700\u8fdb\u884c\u65b0\u51a0\u75c5\u6bd2\u6838\u9178\u68c0\u6d4b{{!}}\u754c\u9762\u65b0\u95fb \u00b7 \u5feb\u8baf|website=www.jiemian.com|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nShenzhen introduced a legislation draft for public comment, intending to ban the consumption of all non-aquatic animals except for nine enumerated.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sz.gov.cn/cn/xxgk/zfxxgj/zwdt/content/post_6740871.html|title=\u6df1\u5733\u7ecf\u6d4e\u7279\u533a\u5168\u9762\u7981\u6b62\u98df\u7528\u91ce\u751f\u52a8\u7269\u6761\u4f8b\u516c\u5f00\u5f81\u6c42\u610f\u89c1--\u653f\u52a1\u52a8\u6001|website=www.sz.gov.cn|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"auto1\"/>\n\n=== 26 February ===\nBeijing required foreign travellers arriving from areas affected by COVID-19 to be quarantined for 14 days.<ref name=\"BeijingCNA26Feb\">{{cite web |title=Beijing orders quarantine for foreign arrivals from virus-hit areas |url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asia/beijing-orders-quarantine-for-foreign-arrivals-from-virus-hit-areas-12473012 |website=CNA |accessdate=26 February 2020 |date=26 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nNational measures were introduced to aid business resumption, clamp down on malicious disruptors of traffic and logistics, and prohibit the excessive raising of essential medical supplies or disruption of market order.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u4f9d\u6cd5\u4fdd\u969c\u75ab\u60c5\u9632\u63a7\u671f\u95f4\u590d\u5de5\u590d\u4ea7 _ \u4e1c\u65b9\u8d22\u5bcc\u7f51 |url=http://finance.eastmoney.com/a/202002271398416421.html |accessdate=28 February 2020 |work=finance.eastmoney.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://m.ce.cn/bwzg/202002/27/t20200227_34352773.shtml|title=\u4e25\u6253\u8fd9\u4e9b\u8fdd\u6cd5\u72af\u7f6a\uff01\u653f\u6cd5\u673a\u5173\u4f9d\u6cd5\u4fdd\u969c\u590d\u5de5\u590d\u4ea7_\u4e2d\u56fd\u7ecf\u6d4e\u7f51|website=m.ce.cn|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nJilin adjusted its emergency response level to level 2,<ref>{{cite news |title=\u5409\u6797\u7701\u65b0\u51a0\u80ba\u708e\u75ab\u60c5\u9632\u63a7\u5e94\u6025\u54cd\u5e94\u7ea7\u522b\u8c03\u6574\u4e3a\u7701\u7ea7\u4e8c\u7ea7\u54cd\u5e94 |url=https://www.jiemian.com/article/4032282.html |accessdate=28 February 2020 |work=www.jiemian.com}}</ref> and Hainan to level 3.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u6d77\u5357\u7a81\u53d1\u516c\u5171\u536b\u751f\u4e8b\u4ef6\u4e00\u7ea7\u54cd\u5e94\u8c03\u6574\u4e3a\u4e09\u7ea7\u54cd\u5e94 |url=https://www.jiemian.com/article/4032414.html |accessdate=28 February 2020 |website=jiemian.com}}</ref> Fujian adjusted its level to level 2 or 3 based on the risk of the region.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jiemian.com/article/4034590.html|title=\u798f\u5efa\u7701\u8c03\u6574\u65b0\u51a0\u80ba\u708e\u75ab\u60c5\u9632\u63a7\u5e94\u6025\u54cd\u5e94\u7b49\u7ea7{{!}}\u754c\u9762\u65b0\u95fb \u00b7 \u5feb\u8baf|website=www.jiemian.com|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n[[Yantai|Yantai, Shandong]] will now test all persons entering China from the city for SARS-CoV-2 for free.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u70df\u53f0\uff1a\u5c06\u5bf9\u6240\u6709\u5165\u5883\u4eba\u5458\u4e00\u5f8b\u5b9e\u884c\u514d\u8d39\u6838\u9178\u68c0\u6d4b\u670d\u52a1{{!}}\u754c\u9762\u65b0\u95fb \u00b7 \u5feb\u8baf |url=https://www.jiemian.com/article/4032138.html |accessdate=28 February 2020 |work=www.jiemian.com}}</ref>\n\n== Reactions and measures outside mainland China ==\n=== 1 February ===\nAustralia's [[Department of Health (Australia)|Department of Health]] issued directives, going into effect from 1 February. Accordingly, travel advisory was increased to level 4: do not travel to all of mainland China. All travellers arriving out of mainland China were asked to self-isolate for a period of 14 days from the time of leaving. Additional border measures were implemented to deny entry of people who have arrived from the mainland China, with the exception of Australian citizens, permanent residents and their immediate family and air crews who have been using appropriate personal protective equipment.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.health.gov.au/news/australian-health-protection-principal-committee-ahppc-novel-coronavirus-statement-on-1-february-2020|title=Australian Health Protection Principal Committee (AHPPC) novel coronavirus statement on 1 February 2020|last=|first=|date=|website=Department of Health (Australia)|language=en|access-date=1 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nInternational border gates [[M\u00f3ng C\u00e1i]] ([[Qu\u1ea3ng Ninh Province]], Vietnam) - [[Dongxing, Guangxi|Dongxing]] (Guangxi, China) ceased functioning on 1 February for an unspecified time; border gates Ho\u00e0nh M\u00f4 and B\u1eafc Phong Sinh experienced a 24-hour closure, awaiting further measurements from authorities.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://vtc.vn/tin-tuc-trong-ngay/quang-ninh-dong-cua-cac-diem-xuat-hang-tren-tuyen-bien-gioi-giap-trung-quoc-ar524858.html|title=Qu\u1ea3ng Ninh \u0111\u00f3ng c\u1eeda c\u00e1c \u0111i\u1ec3m xu\u1ea5t h\u00e0ng tr\u00ean tuy\u1ebfn bi\u00ean gi\u1edbi gi\u00e1p Trung Qu\u1ed1c|last=|first=|date=|language=vi|access-date=31 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200201135903/https://vtc.vn/tin-tuc-trong-ngay/quang-ninh-dong-cua-cac-diem-xuat-hang-tren-tuyen-bien-gioi-giap-trung-quoc-ar524858.html|archive-date=1 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://tuoitre.vn/nguoi-dan-len-mong-cai-de-sang-trung-quoc-duoc-yeu-cau-quay-ve-20200131214355373.htm|title=Ng\u01b0\u1eddi d\u00e2n l\u00ean M\u00f3ng C\u00e1i \u0111\u1ec3 sang Trung Qu\u1ed1c \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c y\u00eau c\u1ea7u quay v\u1ec1|last=|first=|date=31 January 2020|language=vi|access-date=31 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200201130758/https://tuoitre.vn/nguoi-dan-len-mong-cai-de-sang-trung-quoc-duoc-yeu-cau-quay-ve-20200131214355373.htm|archive-date=1 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nTaiwan barred nationals from [[Guangdong]] (mainland China) and travellers who recently visited the area will be subject to a mandatory 14-day quarantine, from entry beginning 1 February.<ref name=\"US FAA\">{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/02/01/world/asia/coronavirus-china.html#link-d768830|title=Coronavirus Live Updates: Vietnam and Australia Curb Access to China as Death Toll Passes 300|last=|first=|date=|language=en|access-date=2 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200202035752/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/02/01/world/asia/coronavirus-china.html#link-d768830|archive-date=2 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nWith the sixth case being another domestic transmission, Vietnamese Prime Minister [[Nguy\u1ec5n Xu\u00e2n Ph\u00fac]] signed an epidemic declaration.<ref name=\"VN declare\" /> Aviation permits which already had been granted for flights between Vietnam and China Mainland-Hong Kong-Macau were all revoked, effective immediately from 13:00 (UTC+7, 1 February) for an unspecified time.<ref name=\"VN declare\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://tuoitre.vn/dung-toan-bo-chuyen-bay-giua-viet-nam-va-trung-quoc-tu-chieu-nay-20200201155919672.htm|title=D\u1eebng to\u00e0n b\u1ed9 chuy\u1ebfn bay gi\u1eefa Vi\u1ec7t Nam v\u00e0 Trung Qu\u1ed1c t\u1eeb chi\u1ec1u nay|last=|first=|date=|website=tuoitre.vn|language=vi|access-date=1 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200201124712/https://tuoitre.vn/dung-toan-bo-chuyen-bay-giua-viet-nam-va-trung-quoc-tu-chieu-nay-20200201155919672.htm|archive-date=1 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> It perhaps lasts until 1 May, according to  the [[United States Federal Aviation Administration]].<ref name=\"US FAA\" />\n\nIndia banned the export of [[N95 masks]] with immediate effect.<ref name=\"Indian N-95 Mask Export Ban\">{{cite web|url=https://www.cityspidey.com/news/11202/with-corona-in-the-backdrop-health-ministry-bans-export-of-n-95-mask|title=N-95 Mask Export Ban! With corona in the backdrop, Health Ministry bans export of N-95 Mask|last=Bhat|first=Nishi|date=1 February 2020|access-date=1 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200201113236/https://www.cityspidey.com/news/11202/with-corona-in-the-backdrop-health-ministry-bans-export-of-n-95-mask|archive-date=1 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe Government of Japan barred: entry of foreign nationals infected with the virus, and entry of Chinese citizens with passports issued in Hubei province.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://japantoday.com/category/national/Japan-bars-entry-of-foreign-travelers-from-China%27s-Hubei-Province|title=Japan bars entry of foreign travelers from China's Hubei Province|last=|first=|date=|website=Japan Today|language=en|access-date=1 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200201193434/https://japantoday.com/category/national/Japan-bars-entry-of-foreign-travelers-from-China%27s-Hubei-Province|archive-date=1 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n102 German citizens and 26 relatives, all of whom were symptom-free on departure, were evacuated from the Wuhan region to [[Frankfurt am Main]] by the [[Executive Transport Wing (German Air Force)|Executive Transport Wing]] of the [[German Air Force]]. After their return, they were placed in quarantine in a military barrack in [[Rhineland-Palatinate]] for 14 days.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tagesschau.de/inland/coronavirus-germersheim-107.html|title=Nach Flug aus China: Zwei Corona-Infizierte in S\u00fcdpfalz-Kaserne|last=tagesschau.de|website=tagesschau.de|language=de|access-date=7 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200203041132/https://www.tagesschau.de/inland/coronavirus-germersheim-107.html|archive-date=3 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The coronavirus was found in two passengers on 2 February. On the outward flight, the Bundeswehr aircraft had 10,000 protective suits on board, which were handed over to the Chinese authorities.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sueddeutsche.de/gesundheit/wuhan-bundeswehr-deutsche-spanien-coronavirus-1.4780838|title=Coronavirus: Flug in Frankfurt gelandet|last=Zeitung|first=S\u00fcddeutsche|website=S\u00fcddeutsche.de|language=de|access-date=7 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200202084353/https://www.sueddeutsche.de/gesundheit/wuhan-bundeswehr-deutsche-spanien-coronavirus-1.4780838|archive-date=2 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sueddeutsche.de/wissen/forschung-wuhan-evakuierungsflug-aus-china-nach-umweg-gelandet-dpa.urn-newsml-dpa-com-20090101-200201-99-728781|title=Evakuierungsflug aus China nach Umweg gelandet|last=Zeitung|first=S\u00fcddeutsche|website=S\u00fcddeutsche.de|language=de|access-date=7 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200202083617/https://www.sueddeutsche.de/wissen/forschung-wuhan-evakuierungsflug-aus-china-nach-umweg-gelandet-dpa.urn-newsml-dpa-com-20090101-200201-99-728781|archive-date=2 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nTrinidad and Tobago's travel restrictions on persons arriving from China goes into full effect. Persons now have to wait 14 days after leaving China before being able to enter Trinidad & Tobago. Additionally persons who may already be at a port of entry and who were in China or are showing symptoms will be subject to quarantine measures. Thermal screening is also being conducted on passengers arriving from Canada, Panama, the United Kingdom and the United States. Testing will also be done by the [[Caribbean Public Health Agency]] (CARPHA) on 3 February.<ref name=\"TT Coronavirus travel ban now in effect\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.guardian.co.tt/neo/NeoProxy.dll?app=NeoDirect&com=6/2/1044268/3e2e11acfd|title=Coronavirus travel ban now in effect|website=www.guardian.co.tt}}</ref>\n\n[[Qatar Airways]] has suspended flights to mainland China from 3 February until further notice.<ref name=\"Qatar Airways suspends flights\">{{cite web|url=https://business.financialpost.com/pmn/business-pmn/qatar-air-suspends-flights-to-china-as-cases-jump-virus-update|title=Qatar Air Suspends Flights to China as Cases Jump: Virus Update|last=|first=|date=1 February 2020|publisher=Financial Post|access-date=1 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200202125324/https://business.financialpost.com/pmn/business-pmn/qatar-air-suspends-flights-to-china-as-cases-jump-virus-update|archive-date=2 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"Qatar Airways suspends flights\" /> It is the first air carrier in the Middle East to do so.\n\n[[Princess Cruises]] announces restrictions on crew members and guests who have recently travelled within mainland China. Guests who have traveled through or in mainland China 14 days prior to the scheduled departure of their cruise will not be allowed to board. Crew members from mainland China are prohibited from getting on any ship until further notice from the company. Crew members scheduled on connecting flights to China have been rerouted. Two cruises in June have been cancelled and two cruises have been rerouted to arrive or depart in [[Tokyo]] instead of Shanghai.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/asia/live-news/coronavirus-outbreak-02-01-20-intl-hnk/index.html|title=Cruise line announces restrictions on passengers who were in China|last1=Chen|first1=Natasha|website=CNN|publisher=Turner Broadcasting System, Inc.|accessdate=1 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200201030034/https://www.cnn.com/asia/live-news/coronavirus-outbreak-02-01-20-intl-hnk/index.html|archive-date=1 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n=== 2 February ===\nNew Zealand has temporarily banned all foreign nationals travelling from, or transiting through mainland China after 2 February to assist the containment of the coronavirus into New Zealand and the Pacific Islands. Foreign travelers in transit to New Zealand on 2 February will be subject to enhanced scanning but pending clearance will be allowed into New Zealand. New Zealand citizens and permanent residents, and their immediate family members, will be allowed to enter New Zealand but must self-isolate for 14 days. The ban will last for 14 days but will be reviewed every 48 hours.<ref>{{cite news|last=Feek|first=Belinda|url=https://www.nzherald.co.nz/nz/news/article.cfm?c_id=1&objectid=12305282|title=Coronavirus: NZ Government to block travellers from mainland China, as details of recovery mission revealed|date=2 February 2020|work=[[New Zealand Herald]]|access-date=2 February 2019|location=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200202071209/https://www.nzherald.co.nz/nz/news/article.cfm?c_id=1&objectid=12305282|archive-date=2 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.rnz.co.nz/news/national/408675/nz-to-close-doors-on-foreign-travellers-from-china|title=NZ to close doors on foreign travellers from China|date=2 February 2020|work=[[Radio New Zealand]]|access-date=|location=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200202043654/https://www.rnz.co.nz/news/national/408675/nz-to-close-doors-on-foreign-travellers-from-china|archive-date=2 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe Philippines has temporarily banned foreigners arriving from China and its territories, including those who visited such areas within the past 14 days, from entering the country; Filipino citizens and permanent residents of the Philippines arriving from such would have to undergo quarantine for 14 days. Travel from Philippines to China and its territories have been temporarily banned as well.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/news/02/02/20/ph-imposes-travel-ban-on-china-as-new-coronavirus-infections-rise-globally|title=PH imposes travel ban on China as new coronavirus infections rise globally|website=ABS-CBN News|language=en|access-date=2 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200205134435/https://news.abs-cbn.com/news/02/02/20/ph-imposes-travel-ban-on-china-as-new-coronavirus-infections-rise-globally|archive-date=5 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nAccording to a diplomatic note distributed to foreign residents in [[North Korea]], North Korean authorities have suspended the flight route between [[Pyongyang]] and [[Vladivostok]] performed by [[Air Koryo]]\u2019s.<ref name=\"auto14\">{{cite web|url=https://www.nknews.org/2020/02/north-korea-suspends-vladivostok-flights-expands-virus-containment-measures/|title=North Korea suspends Vladivostok flights, expands virus containment measures|last1=O'Carroll|first1=Chad|publisher=NKNEWS|language=en|format=2020-02-01|accessdate=2 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200202201532/https://www.nknews.org/2020/02/north-korea-suspends-vladivostok-flights-expands-virus-containment-measures/|archive-date=2 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> According to the same note \"During the month of February, events, ceremonial visits and meetings shall not proceed, and essential meetings shall be conducted via telephone\" [...] all diplomats or international organization staff going to North Korea will now be subjected to a mandatory 15-day quarantine process at their \"place of residence\" from the day of arrival\".<ref name=\"auto14\" /> Those subject to quarantine by North Korean authorities will not be allowed to come into contact with other persons and must not enter public places.<ref name=\"auto14\" /> KCNA reported all people who entered the country after 13 January to have been placed under \"medical supervision.\"<ref name=\"edition.cnn.com\">{{cite news|last1=Berlinger|first1=Joshua|url=https://edition.cnn.com/2020/02/06/asia/north-korea-wuhan-coronavirus-infection-intl-hnk/index.html|title=All of its neighbors have it, so why hasn't North Korea reported any coronavirus cases?|date=7 February 2020|accessdate=7 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200207093221/https://edition.cnn.com/2020/02/06/asia/north-korea-wuhan-coronavirus-infection-intl-hnk/index.html|archive-date=7 February 2020|publisher=CNN|last2=Seo|first2=Yoonjung}}</ref>\n\nSouth Korean Prime Minister [[Chung Sye-kyun]] announced to the public the entry barring of all foreign nationals, who have been to Hubei Province since 21 January, will go into effect starting 4 February for an unspecified time. Also, the visa-free policy for Chinese citizens to visit [[Jeju Island]] is to be temporarily nullified.<ref>{{citation|last=|first=|title=Korea to ban entry from China's Hubei province|date=|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20200202000194|website=Korea Herald|location=Seoul, South Korea|access-date=2 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200206082303/http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20200202000194|archive-date=6 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIndonesia banned all flights from and to Mainland China starting from 5 February. The government also stopped giving free visa and visa on arrival for Chinese nationals. They banned those who live or stay in Mainland China for at least 14 days before from entering or transiting Indonesia. Indonesians are discouraged from travelling to China.<ref>{{citation|last=|first=|title=Indonesia to stop flights to and from China amid coronavirus epidemic|date=|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/amp/news/2020/02/02/indonesia-to-stop-flights-to-and-from-china-amid-coronavirus-epidemic.html|website=The Jakarta Post|location=Jakarta, Indonesia|access-date=2 February 2020|archive-ur