ers Depart Cruise Ship Quarantined Over Coronavirus|date=16 February 2020|work=Wall Street Journal|access-date=17 February 2020|language=en-US|issn=0099-9660}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.msn.com/en-us/news/world/coronavirus-cruise-american-passengers-evacuate-ship-to-return-to-the-us/ar-BB103VDq|title=Coronavirus cruise: American passengers evacuate ship to return to the U.S.|website=www.msn.com|access-date=17 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nSingapore will enforce Stay-Home Notices for all Singapore residents and long-term pass holders returning from China taking effect from 18 February. They will not be allowed to leave home during the next 14 days.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Goh |first1=Timothy |last2=Yuen |first2=Sin |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/health/coronavirus-under-new-stay-home-notice-all-returning-from-china-not-allowed-to |title=Coronavirus: Under S'pore's new Stay-Home Notice, all returning from China not allowed to leave home for 14 days |date=17 February 2020 |website=The Straits Times |access-date=17 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nFollowing the confirmation of infection aboard the [[MS Westerdam|MS ''Westerdam'']], the Malaysian authorities barred passengers who had traveled on the luxury cruise ship from entry.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-02-16/malaysia-bars-westerdam-passengers-cancels-special-u-s-flights |title=Malaysia Bars Westerdam Cruise Passengers From Entry |website=Bloomberg |access-date=17 February 2020}}</ref> Singapore follows suit, only allowing citizens to enter with quarantine imposed.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Yuen |first1=Sin |last2=Tay |first2=Tiffany Fumiko |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/coronavirus-two-singaporeans-from-westerdam-cruise-ship-under-quarantine-here-no-other |title=Coronavirus: Two Singaporeans from Westerdam cruise ship under quarantine here; no other passengers allowed in |date=17 February 2020 |website=The Straits Times |access-date=17 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n[[Naruhito|Japanese Emperor Naruhito]]'s birthday ceremony and greetings to the public on 23 February will be cancelled.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www3.nhk.or.jp/nhkworld/en/news/20200217_36/ |title=Emperor Naruhito's birthday greeting cancelled |website=NHK News |access-date=17 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe Israeli [[Ministry of Health (Israel)|Ministry of Health]] requested people returning from Asian countries and territories to self-quarantine. In the mention are mainland China, Taiwan, Macau, Hong Kong, Singapore, Thailand, South Korea and Japan.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.jpost.com/Israel-News/Are-Israelis-returning-from-Asian-countries-going-quarantine-617830 |title=Are Israelis returning from Asian countries going into quarantine? |website=The Jerusalem Post |access-date=17 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Tokyo Marathon]], due to take place on 1 March, will be restricted to elite runners and wheelchair athletes.<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite news|last=Ingle|first=Sean|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2020/feb/17/tokyo-marathon-restricted-to-elite-runners-over-coronavirus-scare-athletics|title=Tokyo marathon cancels mass race over coronavirus scare|date=17 February 2020|work=The Guardian|access-date=17 February 2020|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref> Initially, it was expected that 38,000 people would take part but with this change the number will be reduced to 206 participants.<ref name=\":3\" />\n\nThe seventh episode of ''[[A Certain Scientific Railgun T]]'', \"Auribus oculi fideliores sunt. (The eyes are more trustworthy than the ears)\", is replaced by a rerun of the sixth episode due to production delays associated with the virus outbreak.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Hodgkins |first1=Crystalyn |title=A Certain Scientific Railgun T Anime's 7th Episode Delayed Due to Effects of Coronavirus |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2020-02-17/a-certain-scientific-railgun-t-anime-7th-episode-delayed-due-to-effects-of-coronavirus/.156535 |website=Anime News 