 Nations Championship]] match with Italy, which was supposed to be held on the weekend of 6 to 8 March, has been postponed due to the coronavirus, and may be cancelled. This comes after a meeting with health officials led by [[Simon Harris (politician)|Simon Harris]], the Health Minister.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Carroll |first1=Rory |title=Ireland v Italy in Six Nations postponed and may be cancelled due to coronavirus |url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2020/feb/26/ireland-v-italy-six-nations-match-postponed-due-to-coronavirus |website=CNA |accessdate=26 February 2020 |date=26 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Badminton World Federation]] announced it has postponed the [[2020 German Open (badminton)|2020 German Open]] and Polish Open tournaments, originally scheduled to be held from 3 to 8 March and 26 to 29 March respectively.<ref>{{cite news |title=BWF Media Statement on Yonex German Open 2020 |url=https://bwfbadminton.com/news-single/2020/02/26/bwf-media-statement-on-yonex-german-open-2020-2/ |publisher=Badminton World Federation |accessdate=2 March 2020 |date=26 February 2020 |work=bwfbadminton.com}}</ref>\n\n[[AnimeJapan]] 2020 was cancelled.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2020/02/26/animejapan-2020-officially-canceled-over-coronavirus-concerns|title=AnimeJapan 2020 Officially Canceled Over Coronavirus Concerns|first=Kyle|last=Cardine|website=[[Crunchyroll]]}}</ref>\n\nChinese authorities confiscated more than 31 million counterfeit surgical masks.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.businessinsider.com/coronavirus-china-confiscated-over-31-million-counterfeit-face-masks-report-2020-2|title=China confiscated over 31 million counterfeit face masks as coronavirus fears cause supply shortage and spike in demand|first=Jessica|last=Snouwaert|website=Business Insider}}</ref>\n\nUS [[Centers for Disease Control and Prevention]] (CDC) has confirmed an infection in California in a person who reportedly did not have relevant travel history or exposure to another known patient with COVID-19. The patient\u2019s exposure is unknown.\u00a0 It\u2019s possible this could be the  first instance of community spread in the US. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cdc.gov/media/releases/2020/s0226-Covid-19-spread.html|title=Coronavirus Disease 2019|date=2020-02-28|website=Centers for Disease Control and Prevention|language=en-us|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>. At the press briefings, President trump remarked that \"As of today, we have 15 cases of COVID-19 that have been detected in the US, with only one new case detected in the last two weeks\" , \"the 15 within a couple of days is going to be down to close to zero\", \"Over the last 10 years, we\u2019ve lost 360,000.\u00a0 These are people that have died from the flu\" and \"He (President Xi)  is working so hard...And they\u2019re calling up Dr. Fauci.\u00a0 They\u2019re calling up our people.\u00a0 We\u2019re dealing with them.\u00a0 We\u2019re giving them certain advice.\u00a0 We actually have \u2014 through World Health, we have them over there also.\u00a0 And we have a lot of our people making up that group that went over there.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.whitehouse.gov/briefings-statements/remarks-president-trump-vice-president-pence-members-coronavirus-task-force-press-conference/|title=Remarks by President Trump, Vice President Pence, and Members of the Coronavirus Task Force in Press Conference|website=The White House|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n\n===27 February===\nSaudi Arabia banned pilgrims and foreigners from entering the country due to the coronavirus.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Giordano |first1=Chiara |title=Coronavirus: Saudi Arabia bans foreigners from entering country to make pilgrimage to holy sites |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/middle-east/coronavirus-saudi-arabia-pilgrim-religious-foreign-ban-umrah-hajj-mecca-symptoms-a9362326.html |website=The Independent |accessdate=27 February 2020 |date=27 February 2020}}</ref>\n\